\"No initial access tokens\"},{\"key\":\"redirectUrl\",\"value\":\"Redirect URL\"},{\"key\":\"notBefore\",\"value\":\"Not Before\"},{\"key\":\"otpSupportedApplications.totpAppMicrosoftAuthenticatorName\",\"value\":\"Microsoft Authenticator\"},{\"key\":\"error-invalid-length-too-long\",\"value\":\"'{{0}}' must have maximal length of {{2}}.\"},{\"key\":\"included.client.audience.label\",\"value\":\"Included Client Audience\"},{\"key\":\"tableTitle\",\"value\":\"Attributes groups\"},{\"key\":\"invalidPasswordNotContainsUsernameMessage\",\"value\":\"Invalid password: Can not contain the username.\"},{\"key\":\"generateNewKeys\",\"value\":\"Generate new keys\"},{\"key\":\"validateRealm\",\"value\":\"You must enter a realm\"},{\"key\":\"revokeRefreshToken\",\"value\":\"Revoke Refresh Token\"},{\"key\":\"noIdentityProviderInstructions\",\"value\":\"There are no identity providers yet in this realm. If you want to link an identity provider with this organization, please go to the \\\"Identity providers\\\" section in the left navigation bar and create an identity provider\"},{\"key\":\"selectAll\",\"value\":\"Select all\"},{\"key\":\"protocolTypes.openid-connect\",\"value\":\"OpenID Connect\"},{\"key\":\"addOpenIdProvider\",\"value\":\"Add OpenID Connect provider\"},{\"key\":\"memory\",\"value\":\"Memory\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.FEDERATED_IDENTITY_OVERRIDE_LINK.name\",\"value\":\"Federated identity link override\"},{\"key\":\"attributeName\",\"value\":\"Attribute [Name]\"},{\"key\":\"importUsersHelp\",\"value\":\"If true, LDAP users will be imported into the Keycloak DB and synced by the configured sync policies.\"},{\"key\":\"hours\",\"value\":\"Hours\"},{\"key\":\"removeConfirm_other\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to remove these groups.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_EMAIL_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Update email error\"},{\"key\":\"searchScopeHelp\",\"value\":\"For one level, the search applies only for users in the DNs specified by User DNs. For subtree, the search applies to the whole subtree. See LDAP documentation for more details.\"},{\"key\":\"jumpToSection\",\"value\":\"Jump to section\"},{\"key\":\"temporaryLockedHelp\",\"value\":\"The user may be locked due to multiple failed attempts to log in.\"},{\"key\":\"useEntityDescriptorHelp\",\"value\":\"Import metadata from a remote IDP SAML entity descriptor.\"},{\"key\":\"decisionStrategies.CONSENSUS\",\"value\":\"Consensus\"},{\"key\":\"saveProviderSuccess\",\"value\":\"The provider has been saved successfully.\"},{\"key\":\"discoveryEndpointHelp\",\"value\":\"Import metadata from a remote IDP discovery descriptor.\"},{\"key\":\"required\",\"value\":\"Required field\"},{\"key\":\"credentialResetBtn\",\"value\":\"Credential Reset\"},{\"key\":\"userList\",\"value\":\"User list\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.RESET_PASSWORD.name\",\"value\":\"Reset password\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientProfileConfirm\",\"value\":\"This action will permanently delete the profile {{profileName}}. This cannot be undone.\"},{\"key\":\"signServiceProviderMetadataHelp\",\"value\":\"Enable/disable signature of the provider SAML metadata.\"},{\"key\":\"fullSyncPeriodHelp\",\"value\":\"Period for full synchronization in seconds\"},{\"key\":\"sessions\",\"value\":\"Sessions\"},{\"key\":\"encryptionAlgorithmHelp\",\"value\":\"Encryption algorithm, which is used by SAML IDP for encryption of SAML documents, assertions or IDs. The corresponding decryption key for decrypt SAML document parts will be chosen based on this configured algorithm and should be available in realm keys for the encryption (ENC) usage. If algorithm is not configured, then any supported algorithm is allowed and decryption key will be chosen based on the algorithm configured in SAML document itself.\"},{\"key\":\"selectALocale\",\"value\":\"Select a locale\"},{\"key\":\"priority\",\"value\":\"Priority\"},{\"key\":\"bruteForceMode.PermanentAfterTemporaryLockout\",\"value\":\"Lockout permanently after temporary lockout\"},{\"key\":\"policyCodeHelp\",\"value\":\"The JavaScript code providing the conditions for this policy.\"},{\"key\":\"clearAllFilters\",\"value\":\"Clear all filters\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.clients.map-roles-composite-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if an administrator can apply roles defined by this client as a composite to another role\"},{\"key\":\"searchForUser\",\"value\":\"Search user\"},{\"key\":\"clearRealmCacheHelp\",\"value\":\"This will clear entries for all realms.\"},{\"key\":\"useDiscoveryEndpoint\",\"value\":\"Use discovery endpoint\"},{\"key\":\"disablePolicyConfirm\",\"value\":\"Users and clients can't access the policy if it's disabled. Are you sure you want to continue?\"},{\"key\":\"logoutAllDescription\",\"value\":\"If you sign out all active sessions, active subjects in this realm will be signed out.\"},{\"key\":\"flow-type.form-flow\",\"value\":\"Form\"},{\"key\":\"policyRolesHelp\",\"value\":\"Click on 'Add roles' to include accepted roles for this policy. Checking the 'required field' checkbox on a role indicates that the selected role MUST be present while evaluating policy, regardless of other roles. Leaving all relevant roles for the policy unchecked is the equivalent of setting a decision strategy of 'Affirmative'.\"},{\"key\":\"useKerberosForPasswordAuthenticationHelp\",\"value\":\"Use Kerberos login module for authenticating username/password against Kerberos server instead of authenticating against LDAP server with Directory Service API\"},{\"key\":\"guiOrderHelp\",\"value\":\"Specify order of the provider in GUI (such as in Consent page) as integer\"},{\"key\":\"signDocumentsHelp\",\"value\":\"Should SAML documents be signed by the realm?\"},{\"key\":\"resetPassword\",\"value\":\"Reset password\"},{\"key\":\"requireSslHelp\",\"value\":\"Is HTTPS required? 'None' means HTTPS is not required for any client IP address. 'External requests' means localhost and private IP addresses can access without HTTPS. 'All requests' means HTTPS is required for all IP addresses.\"},{\"key\":\"manageServiceAccountUser\",\"value\":\"To manage detail and group mappings, click on the username <1>{{link}}</1>\"},{\"key\":\"helpDisabled\",\"value\":\"Help off\"},{\"key\":\"validRequestURIsHelp\",\"value\":\"List of valid URIs, which can be used as values of 'request_uri' parameter during OpenID Connect authentication request. There is support for the same capabilities like for Valid Redirect URIs. For example wildcards or relative paths.\"},{\"key\":\"emptyAddClientScopesInstructions\",\"value\":\"There are no client scopes left to add\"},{\"key\":\"changeTypeIntro\",\"value\":\"{{count}} selected client scopes will be changed to\"},{\"key\":\"inputType\",\"value\":\"Input type\"},{\"key\":\"clientSecret\",\"value\":\"Client Secret\"},{\"key\":\"claimHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of claim to search for in token. You can reference nested claims by using a '.', i.e. 'address.locality'. To use dot (.) literally, escape it with backslash. (\\\\.)\"},{\"key\":\"regexClaimValues\",\"value\":\"Regex Claim Values\"},{\"key\":\"createGroup\",\"value\":\"Create group\"},{\"key\":\"validatingPublicKeyId\",\"value\":\"Validating public key id\"},{\"key\":\"created\",\"value\":\"Created\"},{\"key\":\"usersDN\",\"value\":\"Users DN\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_POST_LOGIN_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Identity provider post login error\"},{\"key\":\"emptyStateMessage\",\"value\":\"No attributes groups\"},{\"key\":\"addOrganizationAttributes.label\",\"value\":\"Add organization attributes\"},{\"key\":\"waitIncrementSeconds\",\"value\":\"Wait increment\"},{\"key\":\"requiredForLabel.admins\",\"value\":\"Only admins\"},{\"key\":\"clientPolicySearch\",\"value\":\"Search client policy\"},{\"key\":\"claimFilterValue\",\"value\":\"Essential claim value\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REGISTER_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Register error\"},{\"key\":\"missingLastNameMessage\",\"value\":\"'{{0}}': Please specify last name.\"},{\"key\":\"attributeValueHelp\",\"value\":\"Value the attribute must have. If the attribute is a list, then the value must be contained in the list.\"},{\"key\":\"introduction\",\"value\":\"If you want to leave this page and manage this realm, please click the corresponding menu items in the left navigation bar.\"},{\"key\":\"policyEnforcementModes.ENFORCING\",\"value\":\"Enforcing\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnPolicyRequireResidentKey\",\"value\":\"Require discoverable credential\"},{\"key\":\"unlockUsersConfirm\",\"value\":\"All the users that are temporarily locked will be unlocked.\"},{\"key\":\"linkError\",\"value\":\"Could not link identity provider to organization: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"groupsClaim\",\"value\":\"Groups claim\"},{\"key\":\"frontchannelLogoutUrlHelp\",\"value\":\"URL that will cause the client to log itself out when a logout request is sent to this realm (via end_session_endpoint). If not provided, it defaults to the base url.\"},{\"key\":\"requiredActions\",\"value\":\"Required actions\"},{\"key\":\"kc.identity.authc.method\",\"value\":\"Authentication Method\"},{\"key\":\"keyForCodeExchange\",\"value\":\"Proof Key for Code Exchange Code Challenge Method\"},{\"key\":\"clientProfiles\",\"value\":\"Client profiles\"},{\"key\":\"selectUserInfoResponseEncryptionContentEncryptionAlgorithm\",\"value\":\"Select user info response encryption content encryption algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"overwritten\",\"value\":\"Overwritten\"},{\"key\":\"deleteProviderError\",\"value\":\"Error deleting the provider: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"generatedIdTokenIsDisabled\",\"value\":\"Generated id token is disabled when no user is selected\"},{\"key\":\"nodeHost\",\"value\":\"Node host\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REGISTER_NODE_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Register node error\"},{\"key\":\"eventListenersHelpTextHelp\",\"value\":\"Configure what listeners receive events for the realm.\"},{\"key\":\"acrToLoAMapping\",\"value\":\"ACR to LoA Mapping\"},{\"key\":\"clientRedirectURIsIllegalSchemeError\",\"value\":\"A redirect URI uses an illegal scheme\"},{\"key\":\"forcePostBindingHelp\",\"value\":\"Always use POST binding for responses.\"},{\"key\":\"executorName\",\"value\":\"Name\"},{\"key\":\"VERIFY_EMAIL\",\"value\":\"Verify Email (VERIFY_EMAIL)\"},{\"key\":\"updateClientProfilesSuccess\",\"value\":\"The client profiles configuration was updated\"},{\"key\":\"admin-clearEventsHelp\",\"value\":\"Deletes all admin events in the database.\"},{\"key\":\"removeImported\",\"value\":\"Remove imported\"},{\"key\":\"endpoints\",\"value\":\"Endpoints\"},{\"key\":\"validatingX509CertsHelp\",\"value\":\"The public certificates Keycloak uses to validate the signatures of SAML requests and responses from the external IDP when Use metadata descriptor URL is OFF. Multiple certificates can be entered separated by comma (,). The certificates can be re-imported from the Metadata descriptor URL clicking the Import Keys action in the identity provider page. The action downloads the current certificates in the metadata endpoint and assigns them to the config in this same option. You need to click Save to definitely store the re-imported certificates.\"},{\"key\":\"samlCapabilityConfig\",\"value\":\"SAML capabilities\"},{\"key\":\"periodicChangedUsersSyncHelp\",\"value\":\"Whether periodic synchronization of changed or newly created LDAP users to Keycloak should be enabled or not\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopesRolesScope\",\"value\":\"If there is no role scope mapping defined, each user is permitted to use this client scope. If there are role scope mappings defined, the user must be a member of at least one of the roles.\"},{\"key\":\"addProvider_one\",\"value\":\"Add {{provider}} provider\"},{\"key\":\"organizationRemoveConfirm_other\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to remove user from the {{count}} selected organizations?\"},{\"key\":\"clientPoliciesPolicies\",\"value\":\"Client Policies Policies\"},{\"key\":\"flowCreatedSuccess\",\"value\":\"Flow created\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.DELETE_ACCOUNT_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Delete account error\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_DELETE_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Client delete error\"},{\"key\":\"test\",\"value\":\"Test\"},{\"key\":\"leaveGroup_one\",\"value\":\"Leave group {{name}}?\"},{\"key\":\"noPasswordPoliciesInstructions\",\"value\":\"You haven't added any password policies to this realm. Add a policy to get started.\"},{\"key\":\"testAuthentication\",\"value\":\"Test authentication\"},{\"key\":\"valueLabel\",\"value\":\"Value\"},{\"key\":\"expiration\",\"value\":\"Expiration\"},{\"key\":\"resourceTypes\",\"value\":\"Resource types\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_PROFILE_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Update profile error\"},{\"key\":\"includeInUserInfo.label\",\"value\":\"Add to userinfo\"},{\"key\":\"back\",\"value\":\"Back\"},{\"key\":\"enableClientSignatureRequiredExplain\",\"value\":\"If you enable \\\"Client signature required\\\", the adapter of this client will be updated. You may need to download a new adapter for this client. You need to generate or import keys for this client otherwise the authentication will not work.\"},{\"key\":\"policiesConfigTypes.formView\",\"value\":\"Form view\"},{\"key\":\"residentKey.No\",\"value\":\"No\"},{\"key\":\"nodeReRegistrationTimeout\",\"value\":\"Node Re-registration timeout\"},{\"key\":\"fineGrainSamlEndpointConfigHelp\",\"value\":\"This section to configure exact URLs for Assertion Consumer and Single Logout Service.\"},{\"key\":\"loginWithEmailHelpText\",\"value\":\"Allow users to log in with their email address.\"},{\"key\":\"deleteMessageBundleSuccess\",\"value\":\"Successfully removed the message from the bundle\"},{\"key\":\"selectAttributes\",\"value\":\"Select attributes\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VERIFY_PROFILE.description\",\"value\":\"Verify profile\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.EXECUTE_ACTIONS.name\",\"value\":\"Execute actions\"},{\"key\":\"encryptAssertions\",\"value\":\"Encrypt assertions\"},{\"key\":\"saveEventListeners\",\"value\":\"Save Event Listeners\"},{\"key\":\"capabilityConfig\",\"value\":\"Capability config\"},{\"key\":\"bindFlow\",\"value\":\"Bind flow\"},{\"key\":\"duplicateGroupWarning\",\"value\":\"Duplication of groups with a large number of subgroups is not supported. Please ensure that the group you are duplicating does not have a large number of subgroups.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.OAUTH2_DEVICE_AUTH_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"OAuth2 device authentication error\"},{\"key\":\"unlinkUsers\",\"value\":\"Unlink users\"},{\"key\":\"identityBrokeringLink\",\"value\":\"Identity brokering link\"},{\"key\":\"clientAuthenticatorTypeHelp\",\"value\":\"Client Authenticator used for authentication of this client against Keycloak server\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CUSTOM_REQUIRED_ACTION_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Custom required action error\"},{\"key\":\"requiredFor\",\"value\":\"Required for\"},{\"key\":\"generatedCodeTextArea\",\"value\":\"Generated code textarea\"},{\"key\":\"searchForAdminEvent\",\"value\":\"Search admin event\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.GRANT_CONSENT_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Grant consent error\"},{\"key\":\"deleteCredentialsError\",\"value\":\"Error deleting users credentials: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"authDefaultActionTooltip\",\"value\":\"If enabled, any new user will have this required action assigned to it.\"},{\"key\":\"validateBindCredentials\",\"value\":\"You must enter the password of the LDAP admin\"},{\"key\":\"samlAttributeToRole\",\"value\":\"If an attribute exists, grant the user the specified realm or client role.\"},{\"key\":\"enableStartTls\",\"value\":\"Enable StartTLS\"},{\"key\":\"createPermissionSuccess\",\"value\":\"Successfully created the permission\"},{\"key\":\"contentSecurityPolicyReportOnly\",\"value\":\"Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REVOKE_GRANT_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Revoke grant error\"},{\"key\":\"status\",\"value\":\"Status\"},{\"key\":\"dragInstruction\",\"value\":\"Click and drag to change priority\"},{\"key\":\"invalidPasswordRegexPatternMessage\",\"value\":\"Invalid password: fails to match regex pattern(s).\"},{\"key\":\"selectResource\",\"value\":\"Select resource\"},{\"key\":\"clientName\",\"value\":\"Name\"},{\"key\":\"clearFile\",\"value\":\"Clear this file\"},{\"key\":\"fetchRolesHelp\",\"value\":\"By default, only the roles available from the token sent with the authorization requests are used to check if the user is granted with a role. If this setting is enabled, the policy will ignore roles from the token and check any role associated with the user instead.\"},{\"key\":\"providerUpdatedError\",\"value\":\"Could not update client policy due to {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"error-invalid-uri-fragment\",\"value\":\"'{{0}}' is invalid URL fragment.\"},{\"key\":\"fromDisplayName\",\"value\":\"From display name\"},{\"key\":\"selectGroup\",\"value\":\"Select group\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.groups.view-members-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if an administrator can view the members of this group\"},{\"key\":\"targetOptions.brokerId\",\"value\":\"BROKER_ID\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VERIFY_PROFILE.name\",\"value\":\"Verify profile\"},{\"key\":\"forwardParameters\",\"value\":\"Forwarded query parameters\"},{\"key\":\"oAuthMutualHelp\",\"value\":\"This enables support for OAuth 2.0 Mutual TLS Certificate Bound Access Tokens, which means that keycloak bind an access token and a refresh token with a X.509 certificate of a token requesting client exchanged in mutual TLS between keycloak's Token Endpoint and this client. These tokens can be treated as Holder-of-Key tokens instead of bearer tokens.\"},{\"key\":\"redirectWhenEmailMatchesHelp\",\"value\":\"Automatically redirect the user to this identity provider when the email domain matches the domain\"},{\"key\":\"scopes\",\"value\":\"Scopes\"},{\"key\":\"flowType\",\"value\":\"Flow type\"},{\"key\":\"invalidPasswordNotEmailMessage\",\"value\":\"Invalid password: must not be equal to the email.\"},{\"key\":\"use\",\"value\":\"Use\"},{\"key\":\"subject\",\"value\":\"Subject DN\"},{\"key\":\"searchClientAuthorizationPolicy\",\"value\":\"Search policy\"},{\"key\":\"startTimeHelp\",\"value\":\"Defines the time before which the policy MUST NOT be granted. Only granted if current date/time is after or equal to this value.\"},{\"key\":\"executorClientAuthenticator\",\"value\":\"Executor Client Authenticator\"},{\"key\":\"importKeys\",\"value\":\"Import keys\"},{\"key\":\"userSessionAttributeHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of user session attribute you want to hardcode\"},{\"key\":\"logo\",\"value\":\"Logo\"},{\"key\":\"backchannelLogoutRevokeOfflineSessions\",\"value\":\"Backchannel logout revoke offline sessions\"},{\"key\":\"managePriorityInfo\",\"value\":\"Priority is the order of providers when doing a user lookup. You can drag the row handlers to change the priorities.\"},{\"key\":\"included.custom.audience.tooltip\",\"value\":\"This is used just if 'Included Client Audience' is not filled. The specified value will be included in audience (aud) field of the token. If there are existing audiences in the token, the specified value is just added to them. It won't override existing audiences.\"},{\"key\":\"registrationAccessTokenHelp\",\"value\":\"The registration access token provides access for clients to the client registration service.\"},{\"key\":\"profilesConfigTypes.formView\",\"value\":\"Form view\"},{\"key\":\"canonicalization\",\"value\":\"Canonicalization method\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmTitle\",\"value\":\"Delete realm?\"},{\"key\":\"SSOSessionMax\",\"value\":\"SSO Session Max\"},{\"key\":\"disableConfirmIdentityProvider\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to disable the provider '{{provider}}'\"},{\"key\":\"client-updater-source-groups.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Name of groups to check. Condition evaluates to true if the entity, who creates/updates client is member of some of the specified groups. Configured groups are specified by their simple name, which must match to the name of the Keycloak group. No support for group hierarchy is used here.\"},{\"key\":\"ldapRolesDnHelp\",\"value\":\"LDAP DN where roles of this tree are saved. For example, 'ou=finance,dc=example,dc=org'\"},{\"key\":\"providerUpdatedSuccess\",\"value\":\"Client policy updated successfully\"},{\"key\":\"createClientScopeError\",\"value\":\"Could not create client scope: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"deleteRole\",\"value\":\"Delete this role\"},{\"key\":\"SSOSessionSettings\",\"value\":\"SSO Session Settings\"},{\"key\":\"directAccessHelp\",\"value\":\"This enables support for Direct Access Grants, which means that client has access to username/password of user and exchange it directly with Keycloak server for access token. In terms of OAuth2 specification, this enables support of 'Resource Owner Password Credentials Grant' for this client.\"},{\"key\":\"groupHelp\",\"value\":\"Group to add the user in. Fill the full path of the group including path. For example: '/root-group/child-group'.\"},{\"key\":\"clientPolicyNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Display name of the policy\"},{\"key\":\"addressClaim.country.label\",\"value\":\"User Attribute Name for Country\"},{\"key\":\"downloadType\",\"value\":\"this is information about the download type\"},{\"key\":\"clustering\",\"value\":\"Clustering\"},{\"key\":\"editModeLdapHelp\",\"value\":\"READ_ONLY is a read-only LDAP store. WRITABLE means data will be synced back to LDAP on demand. UNSYNCED means user data will be imported, but not synced back to LDAP.\"},{\"key\":\"signOutAllActiveSessionsQuestion\",\"value\":\"Sign out all active sessions?\"},{\"key\":\"addPostLogoutRedirectUri\",\"value\":\"Add valid post logout redirect URIs\"},{\"key\":\"noItemsInstructions\",\"value\":\"You haven't created any items in this realm. Create a item to get started.\"},{\"key\":\"unlockSuccess\",\"value\":\"User successfully unlocked\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_CREDENTIAL_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Update credential error\"},{\"key\":\"syncLDAPGroupsError\",\"value\":\"Data could not be synced due {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"resetPasswordConfirmation\",\"value\":\"New password confirmation\"},{\"key\":\"archiveFormat\",\"value\":\"Archive format\"},{\"key\":\"importSuccess\",\"value\":\"New certificate imported\"},{\"key\":\"aggregate.attrs.label\",\"value\":\"Aggregate attribute values\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_FIRST_LOGIN.name\",\"value\":\"Identity provider first login\"},{\"key\":\"enableSwitchSuccess\",\"value\":\"{{switch}} changed successfully\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_INITIATED_ACCOUNT_LINKING_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Client initiated account linking error\"},{\"key\":\"oidcCibaGrantHelp\",\"value\":\"This enables support for OIDC CIBA Grant, which means that the user is authenticated via some external authentication device instead of the user's browser.\"},{\"key\":\"enableSwitchError\",\"value\":\"Could not enable / disable due to {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"clientRegistration\",\"value\":\"Client registration\"},{\"key\":\"samlIdentityProviderMetadata\",\"value\":\"SAML 2.0 Identity Provider Metadata\"},{\"key\":\"validTo\",\"value\":\"Valid to\"},{\"key\":\"addMember\",\"value\":\"Add member\"},{\"key\":\"scopeParameterHelp\",\"value\":\"You can copy/paste this value of scope parameter and use it in initial OpenID Connect Authentication Request sent from this client adapter. Default client scopes and selected optional client scopes will be used when generating token issued for this client\"},{\"key\":\"idTokenEncryptionKeyManagementAlgorithm\",\"value\":\"ID token encryption key management algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"authenticatorAttachment.not specified\",\"value\":\"Not specified\"},{\"key\":\"ssoSessionIdle\",\"value\":\"Time a session is allowed to be idle before it expires. Tokens and browser sessions are invalidated when a session is expired.\"},{\"key\":\"oidcCibaGrant\",\"value\":\"OIDC CIBA Grant\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientSuccess\",\"value\":\"Client profile deleted\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.users.impersonate-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if administrator can impersonate other users\"},{\"key\":\"registerNodeManually\",\"value\":\"Register node manually\"},{\"key\":\"redirectURI\",\"value\":\"Redirect URI\"},{\"key\":\"publicKeys\",\"value\":\"Public keys\"},{\"key\":\"removeConfirmTitle_other\",\"value\":\"Remove groups?\"},{\"key\":\"ldapAttributeValueHelp\",\"value\":\"Value of the LDAP attribute, which will be added to the new user during registration. You can either hardcode any value like 'foo' but you can also use some special tokens. Only supported token right now is '${RANDOM}', which will be replaced with some randomly generated string.\"},{\"key\":\"requireSsl\",\"value\":\"Require SSL\"},{\"key\":\"reevaluate\",\"value\":\"Re-evaluate\"},{\"key\":\"clientOfflineSessionMax\",\"value\":\"Client Offline Session Max\"},{\"key\":\"selectUserInfoResponseEncryptionKeyManagementAlgorithm\",\"value\":\"Select user info response encryption key management algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"batchSizeHelp\",\"value\":\"Count of LDAP users to be imported from LDAP to Keycloak within a single transaction\"},{\"key\":\"addMapperExplain\",\"value\":\"If you want more fine-grain control, you can create protocol mapper on this client\"},{\"key\":\"searchForUserDescription\",\"value\":\"This realm may have a federated provider. Viewing all users may cause the system to slow down, but it can be done by searching for \\\"*\\\". Please search for a user above.\"},{\"key\":\"expirationHelp\",\"value\":\"Sets the expiration for events. Expired events are periodically deleted from the database.\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopeTypes.optional\",\"value\":\"Optional\"},{\"key\":\"validRedirectUri\",\"value\":\"Valid redirect URIs\"},{\"key\":\"userAttribute\",\"value\":\"User Attribute\"},{\"key\":\"revoke\",\"value\":\"Revoke\"},{\"key\":\"admin\",\"value\":\"Admin\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnPolicyAcceptableAaguidsHelp\",\"value\":\"The list of allowed AAGUIDs of which an authenticator can be registered. An AAGUID is a 128-bit identifier indicating the authenticator's type (e.g., make and model).\"},{\"key\":\"jwtX509HeadersEnabled\",\"value\":\"Add X.509 Headers to the JWT\"},{\"key\":\"keyPasswordHelp\",\"value\":\"Password for the private key\"},{\"key\":\"applyPolicyHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies all the policies that must be applied to the scopes defined by this policy or permission.\"},{\"key\":\"sslType.none\",\"value\":\"None\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REVOKE_GRANT.description\",\"value\":\"Revoke grant\"},{\"key\":\"keyPlaceholder\",\"value\":\"Type a key\"},{\"key\":\"senderEnvelopePlaceholder\",\"value\":\"Sender envelope email address\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_RETRIEVE_TOKEN.name\",\"value\":\"Identity provider retrieve token\"},{\"key\":\"groupsDescription\",\"value\":\"A group is a set of attributes and role mappings that can be applied to a user. You can create, edit, and delete groups and manage their child-parent organization.\"},{\"key\":\"organizationRemovedSuccess\",\"value\":\"User removed from organizations\"},{\"key\":\"executorTypeSelectHelpText\",\"value\":\"Executor Type Select Help Text\"},{\"key\":\"createUserProviderError\",\"value\":\"User federation provider could not be created: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"reloadKeysError\",\"value\":\"Error reloading keys. {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"templateHelp\",\"value\":\"Template to use to format the username to import.  Substitutions are enclosed in ${}.  For example: '${ALIAS}.${CLAIM.sub}'.  ALIAS is the provider alias.  CLAIM.<NAME> references an ID or Access token claim. The substitution can be converted to upper or lower case by appending |uppercase or |lowercase to the substituted value, e.g. '${CLAIM.sub | lowercase}\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.USER_DISABLED_BY_PERMANENT_LOCKOUT.description\",\"value\":\"User disabled by permanent lockout\"},{\"key\":\"emptyExecutionInstructions\",\"value\":\"You can start defining this flow by adding a sub-flow or an execution\"},{\"key\":\"invalidPasswordHistoryMessage\",\"value\":\"Invalid password: must not be equal to any of last {0} passwords.\"},{\"key\":\"passwordDataTitle\",\"value\":\"Password data\"},{\"key\":\"accountThemeHelp\",\"value\":\"Select a theme for the user account management console.\"},{\"key\":\"clientSettings\",\"value\":\"Client details\"},{\"key\":\"forgotPasswordHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies independent timeout for forgot password.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VALIDATE_ACCESS_TOKEN_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Validate access token error\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPoliciesHelp.passwordHistory\",\"value\":\"Prevents a recently used password from being reused.\"},{\"key\":\"createClientError\",\"value\":\"Could not create client: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmClientScopes\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to delete this client scope\"},{\"key\":\"authorizationEncryptedResponseAlgHelp\",\"value\":\"JWA Algorithm used for key management in encrypting the authorization response when the response mode is jwt. This option is needed if you want encrypted authorization response. If left empty, the authorization response is just signed, but not encrypted.\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.users.manage-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if an administrator can manage all users in the realm\"},{\"key\":\"oidcSettings\",\"value\":\"OpenID Connect settings\"},{\"key\":\"otpPolicyDigitsHelp\",\"value\":\"How many digits should the OTP have?\"},{\"key\":\"prompts.select_account\",\"value\":\"Select account\"},{\"key\":\"defaultACRValues\",\"value\":\"Default ACR Values\"},{\"key\":\"noConsents\",\"value\":\"No consents\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientPolicyConditionConfirmTitle\",\"value\":\"Delete condition?\"},{\"key\":\"initialCounterErrorHint\",\"value\":\"Value needs to be between 1 and 120\"},{\"key\":\"uiDisplayNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Display name of provider when linked in the Admin UI\"},{\"key\":\"deleteMessageBundle\",\"value\":\"Delete message bundle {{key}}\"},{\"key\":\"viewGuides\",\"value\":\"View guides\"},{\"key\":\"contentSecurityPolicyHelp\",\"value\":\"Default value prevents pages from being included by non-origin iframes <1>Learn more</1>\"},{\"key\":\"organizationDelete\",\"value\":\"Delete organization?\"},{\"key\":\"generatedIdTokenNo\",\"value\":\"No generated id token\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.SEND_RESET_PASSWORD.description\",\"value\":\"Send reset password\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_INITIATED_ACCOUNT_LINKING.name\",\"value\":\"Client initiated account linking\"},{\"key\":\"error-invalid-email\",\"value\":\"Invalid email address.\"},{\"key\":\"partialImport\",\"value\":\"Partial import\"},{\"key\":\"cibaBackhannelTokenDeliveryModes.ping\",\"value\":\"Ping\"},{\"key\":\"includeInTokenScopeHelp\",\"value\":\"If on, the name of this client scope will be added to the access token property 'scope' as well as to the Token Introspection Endpoint response. If off, this client scope will be omitted from the token and from the Token Introspection Endpoint response.\"},{\"key\":\"sync-keycloak-roles-to-ldap\",\"value\":\"Sync Keycloak roles to LDAP\"},{\"key\":\"cacheSettingsDescription\",\"value\":\"This section contains options useful for caching users, which were loaded from this user storage provider.\"},{\"key\":\"couldNotCreateGroup\",\"value\":\"Could not create group {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"disableProvider\",\"value\":\"Disable provider?\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UNREGISTER_NODE.name\",\"value\":\"Unregister node\"},{\"key\":\"saveRealmSuccess\",\"value\":\"Realm created successfully\"},{\"key\":\"createToken\",\"value\":\"Create initial access token\"},{\"key\":\"clientsClientTypeHelp\",\"value\":\"'OpenID Connect' allows Clients to verify the identity of the End-User based on the authentication performed by an Authorization Server.'SAML' enables web-based authentication and authorization scenarios including cross-domain single sign-on (SSO) and uses security tokens containing assertions to pass information.\"},{\"key\":\"noRealmRolesToAssign\",\"value\":\"There are no realm roles to assign\"},{\"key\":\"regexPatternHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies the regex pattern.\"},{\"key\":\"roleHelpHelp\",\"value\":\"Role to grant to user. Click 'Select Role' button to browse roles, or just type it in the textbox. To reference an application role the syntax is appname.approle, i.e. myapp.myrole.\"},{\"key\":\"defaultRoleDeleteError\",\"value\":\"You cannot delete a default role.\"},{\"key\":\"userFedUnlinkUsersConfirm\",\"value\":\"Do you want to unlink all the users? Any users without a password in the database will not be able to authenticate anymore.\"},{\"key\":\"searchUserByAttributeDescription\",\"value\":\"It supports setting multiple attributes as the search filter by setting different keys or values. Only one value can be typed for a key.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.RESET_PASSWORD.description\",\"value\":\"Reset password\"},{\"key\":\"realmSettingsExplain\",\"value\":\"Realm settings are settings that control the options for users, applications, roles, and groups in the current realm.\"},{\"key\":\"exactSearch\",\"value\":\"Exact search\"},{\"key\":\"filenamePlaceholder\",\"value\":\"Upload a PEM file or paste key below\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirm_one\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to delete this group '{{groupName}}'.\"},{\"key\":\"times.seconds\",\"value\":\"Seconds\"},{\"key\":\"removeMappingTitle\",\"value\":\"Remove role?\"},{\"key\":\"userRolesRetrieveStrategy\",\"value\":\"User roles retrieve strategy\"},{\"key\":\"events-disable-title\",\"value\":\"Unsave events?\"},{\"key\":\"MANAGED\",\"value\":\"Managed\"},{\"key\":\"ellipticCurve\",\"value\":\"Elliptic Curve\"},{\"key\":\"unlink\",\"value\":\"Unlink\"},{\"key\":\"emptyAdminEventsInstructions\",\"value\":\"There are no admin events in this realm.\"},{\"key\":\"searchFor\",\"value\":\"Search role by name\"},{\"key\":\"writeOnly\",\"value\":\"Write only\"},{\"key\":\"noGroupsInThisSubGroup\",\"value\":\"No groups in this sub group\"},{\"key\":\"hideMetaData\",\"value\":\"Hide metadata\"},{\"key\":\"themes\",\"value\":\"Themes\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REMOVE_TOTP.name\",\"value\":\"Remove totp\"},{\"key\":\"error-username-invalid-character\",\"value\":\"'{{0}}' contains invalid character.\"},{\"key\":\"serviceProviderEntityIdHelp\",\"value\":\"The Entity ID that will be used to uniquely identify this SAML Service Provider.\"},{\"key\":\"disabledFeatures\",\"value\":\"Disabled features\"},{\"key\":\"itemDeletedSuccess\",\"value\":\"The item has been deleted\"},{\"key\":\"clientUpdaterSourceRolesTooltip\",\"value\":\"The condition is checked during client registration/update requests and it evaluates to true if the entity (usually user), who is creating/updating client is member of the specified role. For reference the realm role, you can use the realm role name like 'my_realm_role' . For reference client role, you can use the client_id.role_name for example 'my_client.my_client_role' will refer to client role 'my_client_role' of client 'my_client'.\"},{\"key\":\"validatorDialogColNames.colName\",\"value\":\"Role name\"},{\"key\":\"deleteExecutorError\",\"value\":\"Could not delete executor: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"version\",\"value\":\"Version\"},{\"key\":\"associatedPermissions\",\"value\":\"Associated permission\"},{\"key\":\"operationType\",\"value\":\"Operation type\"},{\"key\":\"decisionStrategy\",\"value\":\"Decision strategy\"},{\"key\":\"roleMappingUpdatedSuccess\",\"value\":\"Role mapping updated\"},{\"key\":\"securityDefences\",\"value\":\"Security defenses\"},{\"key\":\"realmSettings\",\"value\":\"Realm settings\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VERIFY_EMAIL_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Verify email error\"},{\"key\":\"defaultGroupsHelp\",\"value\":\"Default groups allow you to automatically assign groups membership whenever any new user is created or imported through <1>identity brokering</1>.\"},{\"key\":\"effectiveRoleScopeMappings\",\"value\":\"Effective role scope mappings\"},{\"key\":\"oAuthDeviceCodeLifespanHelp\",\"value\":\"Max time before the device code and user code are expired. This value needs to be a long enough lifetime to be usable (allowing the user to retrieve their secondary device, navigate to the verification URI, login, etc.), but should be sufficiently short to limit the usability of a code obtained for phishing.\"},{\"key\":\"dynamicScopeHelp\",\"value\":\"If on, this scope will be considered a Dynamic Scope, which will be comprised of a static and a variable portion.\"},{\"key\":\"attributePermissionDescription\",\"value\":\"This section contains permissions for who can edit and who can view the attribute.\"},{\"key\":\"editGroupText\",\"value\":\"Edit attributes group\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VERIFY_EMAIL_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Verify email error\"},{\"key\":\"addKeycloakOpenIdProvider\",\"value\":\"Add Keycloak OpenID Connect provider\"},{\"key\":\"authenticatorAttachment.cross-platform\",\"value\":\"Cross platform\"},{\"key\":\"emptyClientScopesInstructions\",\"value\":\"There are currently no client scopes linked to this client. You can add existing client scopes to this client to share protocol mappers and roles.\"},{\"key\":\"cibaInterval\",\"value\":\"Interval\"},{\"key\":\"totalMemory\",\"value\":\"Total memory\"},{\"key\":\"usernameTemplateImporter\",\"value\":\"Format the username to import.\"},{\"key\":\"disableUserInfo\",\"value\":\"Disable user info\"},{\"key\":\"times.minutes\",\"value\":\"Minutes\"},{\"key\":\"authorizationEncryptedResponseEnc\",\"value\":\"Authorization response encryption content encryption algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"forcePostBinding\",\"value\":\"Force POST binding\"},{\"key\":\"leave\",\"value\":\"Leave\"},{\"key\":\"loginSettings\",\"value\":\"Login settings\"},{\"key\":\"notVerified\",\"value\":\"Not verified\"},{\"key\":\"temporaryService\",\"value\":\"Temporary admin service account. Ensure it is replaced with a permanent admin service account as soon as possible.\"},{\"key\":\"multivalued\",\"value\":\"Multivalued\"},{\"key\":\"users\",\"value\":\"Users\"},{\"key\":\"noClientPoliciesInstructions\",\"value\":\"There are no client policies. Select 'Create client policy' to create a new client policy.\"},{\"key\":\"jwksUrlConfig\",\"value\":\"JWKS URL configs\"},{\"key\":\"forceNameIdFormatHelp\",\"value\":\"Ignore requested NameID subject format and use Admin UI configured one.\"},{\"key\":\"bruteForceMode.TemporaryLockout\",\"value\":\"Lockout temporarily\"},{\"key\":\"searchType.attribute\",\"value\":\"Attribute search\"},{\"key\":\"saveProviderError\",\"value\":\"Error saving provider: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"selectACondition\",\"value\":\"Select a condition\"},{\"key\":\"lightweightAccessTokenHelp\",\"value\":\"If it is On, lightweight access tokens are always used. If it is Off, they are not used by default, but it is still possible to enable them with client policy executor\"},{\"key\":\"jwksUrlHelp\",\"value\":\"URL where identity provider keys in JWK format are stored. See JWK specification for more details. If you use external Keycloak identity provider, you can use URL like 'http://broker-keycloak:8180/realms/test/protocol/openid-connect/certs' assuming your brokered Keycloak is running on 'http://broker-keycloak:8180' and its realm is 'test' .\"},{\"key\":\"emptyResources\",\"value\":\"No resources\"},{\"key\":\"ldapSynchronizationSettingsDescription\",\"value\":\"This section contains options related to synchronization of users from LDAP to the Keycloak database.\"},{\"key\":\"roles\",\"value\":\"Roles\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.RESTART_AUTHENTICATION.description\",\"value\":\"Restart authentication\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.users.manage-group-membership-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if an administrator can manage group membership for all users in the realm.  This is used in conjunction with specific group policy\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmRealmSetting\",\"value\":\"If you delete this realm, all associated data will be removed.\"},{\"key\":\"evaluateExplain\",\"value\":\"This page allows you to see all protocol mappers and role scope mappings\"},{\"key\":\"organizationAliasHelp\",\"value\":\"The alias uniquely identifies an organization using a format that is mainly targeted for referencing the organization internally. For instance, when issuing organization-related claims into tokens or when in a custom theme.\"},{\"key\":\"deleteProviderSuccess\",\"value\":\"Success. The provider has been deleted.\"},{\"key\":\"sessionsType.offline\",\"value\":\"Offline\"},{\"key\":\"validatorDeletedError\",\"value\":\"Error saving User Profile: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"preserveGroupInheritance\",\"value\":\"Preserve group inheritance\"},{\"key\":\"createClientScopeSuccess\",\"value\":\"Client scope created\"},{\"key\":\"noRoles-client\",\"value\":\"No roles for this client\"},{\"key\":\"roleMapping\",\"value\":\"Role mapping\"},{\"key\":\"accountLinkingOnlyHelp\",\"value\":\"If true, users cannot log in through this provider.  They can only link to this provider.  This is useful if you don't want to allow login from the provider, but want to integrate with a provider\"},{\"key\":\"localization\",\"value\":\"Localization\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnPolicyRpIdHelp\",\"value\":\"The WebAuthn Relying Party ID (RpID). It must be the origin's effective domain, e.g. 'company.com' or 'auth.company.com'.\"},{\"key\":\"enabledWhen\",\"value\":\"Enabled when\"},{\"key\":\"homeURLHelp\",\"value\":\"Default URL to use when the auth server needs to redirect or link back to the client.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.PUSHED_AUTHORIZATION_REQUEST_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Pushed authorization request error\"},{\"key\":\"importWarning\",\"value\":\"The data and settings imported above may overwrite the data and settings that already exist.\"},{\"key\":\"duplicateEmailsAllowed\",\"value\":\"Duplicate emails\"},{\"key\":\"disableConfirmClient\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to disable this client?\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmUsers_other\",\"value\":\"Delete {{count}} users?\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REMOVE_TOTP_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Remove totp error\"},{\"key\":\"protocolTypes.saml\",\"value\":\"SAML\"},{\"key\":\"displayHeaderHintHelp\",\"value\":\"A user-friendly name for the group that should be used when rendering a group of attributes in user-facing forms. Supports keys for localized values as well. For example: ${profile.attribute.group.address}.\"},{\"key\":\"error-number-out-of-range-too-small\",\"value\":\"'{{0}}' must have minimal value of {{1}}.\"},{\"key\":\"appliedByClients\",\"value\":\"Applied by the following clients\"},{\"key\":\"defaultLocaleHelp\",\"value\":\"The initial locale to use. It is used on the login screen and other screens in the Admin UI and Account UI.\"},{\"key\":\"logoutServiceSoapBindingUrlHelp\",\"value\":\"SAML SOAP Binding URL for the client's single logout service. You can leave this blank if you are using a different binding.\"},{\"key\":\"bruteForceModeHelpText\",\"value\":\"If enabled, specify what should happen to the user account if a brute force attack is detected.\"},{\"key\":\"validatorColNames.colName\",\"value\":\"Validator name\"},{\"key\":\"searchMembers\",\"value\":\"Search members\"},{\"key\":\"keySizeHelp\",\"value\":\"Size for the generated keys\"},{\"key\":\"otpSupportedApplications.totpAppGoogleName\",\"value\":\"Google Authenticator\"},{\"key\":\"editModeKerberosHelp\",\"value\":\"READ_ONLY means that password updates are not allowed and user always authenticates with Kerberos password. UNSYNCED means that the user can change the password in the Keycloak database and this one will be used instead of the Kerberos password.\"},{\"key\":\"invalidateRotatedSecretExplain\",\"value\":\"After invalidating rotated secret, the rotated secret will be removed automatically\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopeDetails\",\"value\":\"Client scope details\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopeRemoveError\",\"value\":\"Could not remove the scope mapping {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"parentId\",\"value\":\"Parent ID\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UNREGISTER_NODE.description\",\"value\":\"Unregister node\"},{\"key\":\"whoWillAppearPopoverTextRoles\",\"value\":\"This tab shows only the users who are assigned directly to this role. To see users who are assigned this role as an associated role or through a group, go to\"},{\"key\":\"shownOnLoginPage\",\"value\":\"Shown on login page\"},{\"key\":\"userObjectClassesHelp\",\"value\":\"All values of LDAP objectClass attribute for users in LDAP, divided by commas. For example: 'inetOrgPerson, organizationalPerson'. Newly created Keycloak users will be written to LDAP with all those object classes and existing LDAP user records are found just if they contain all those object classes.\"},{\"key\":\"setPasswordFor\",\"value\":\"Set password for {{username}}\"},{\"key\":\"updateUserLocale\",\"value\":\"Update User Locale\"},{\"key\":\"whoWillAppearPopoverTextUsers\",\"value\":\"Groups are hierarchical. When you select Direct Membership, you see only the child group that the user joined. Ancestor groups are not included.\"},{\"key\":\"userFedDisableConfirmTitle\",\"value\":\"Disable user federation provider?\"},{\"key\":\"adminURL\",\"value\":\"Admin URL\"},{\"key\":\"singleLogoutServiceUrlHelp\",\"value\":\"The Url that must be used to send logout requests.\"},{\"key\":\"clipboardCopyError\",\"value\":\"Error copying to clipboard.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_REGISTER_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Client register error\"},{\"key\":\"fullSyncPeriod\",\"value\":\"Full sync period\"},{\"key\":\"emptyMembers\",\"value\":\"No members\"},{\"key\":\"mapperUserAttributeName\",\"value\":\"User Attribute Name\"},{\"key\":\"scopeSaveError\",\"value\":\"Could not persist authorization scope due to {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"deletedSuccessIdentityProvider\",\"value\":\"Provider successfully deleted.\"},{\"key\":\"reload\",\"value\":\"Reload\"},{\"key\":\"tokens\",\"value\":\"Tokens\"},{\"key\":\"disabledOff\",\"value\":\"Disabled off\"},{\"key\":\"requirement\",\"value\":\"Requirement\"},{\"key\":\"scopeParameter\",\"value\":\"Scope parameter\"},{\"key\":\"validatingPublicKeyHelp\",\"value\":\"The public key in PEM format that must be used to verify external IDP signatures.\"},{\"key\":\"backchannelUrlInvalid\",\"value\":\"Backchannel logout URL is not a valid URL\"},{\"key\":\"accessTokenSuccess\",\"value\":\"Access token regenerated\"},{\"key\":\"allowPasswordAuthentication\",\"value\":\"Allow password authentication\"},{\"key\":\"privateRSAKey\",\"value\":\"Private RSA Key\"},{\"key\":\"requirements.ALTERNATIVE\",\"value\":\"Alternative\"},{\"key\":\"consentScreenTextHelp\",\"value\":\"Text that will be shown on the consent screen when this client scope is added to some client with consent required. Defaults to name of client scope if it is not filled\"},{\"key\":\"roleList\",\"value\":\"Role list\"},{\"key\":\"kerberosRealm\",\"value\":\"Kerberos realm\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VALIDATE_ACCESS_TOKEN.name\",\"value\":\"Validate access token\"},{\"key\":\"contextualAttributes\",\"value\":\"Contextual Attributes\"},{\"key\":\"replyTo\",\"value\":\"Reply to\"},{\"key\":\"downloadAdapterConfig\",\"value\":\"Download adapter config\"},{\"key\":\"allowEcpFlow\",\"value\":\"Allow ECP flow\"},{\"key\":\"addExecutorError\",\"value\":\"Executor not created: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.clients.manage-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if an administrator can manage this client\"},{\"key\":\"idpInitiatedSsoRelayState\",\"value\":\"IDP Initiated SSO Relay State\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopesConditionTooltip\",\"value\":\"The list of expected client scopes. Condition evaluates to true if specified client request matches some of the client scopes. It depends also whether it should be default or optional client scope based on the 'Scope Type' configured.\"},{\"key\":\"unlinkError\",\"value\":\"Could not unlink identity provider from organization: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VALIDATE_ACCESS_TOKEN_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Validate access token error\"},{\"key\":\"deletedErrorRealmSetting\",\"value\":\"Could not delete realm: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"consensus\",\"value\":\"Consensus\"},{\"key\":\"emptyEvents\",\"value\":\"Nothing to add\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.SEND_IDENTITY_PROVIDER_LINK.name\",\"value\":\"Send identity provider link\"},{\"key\":\"SSOSessionIdleRememberMe\",\"value\":\"SSO Session Idle Remember Me\"},{\"key\":\"cibaBackchannelTokenDeliveryModeHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies how the CD (Consumption Device) gets the authentication result and related tokens. This mode will be used by default for the CIBA clients, which do not have other mode explicitly set.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REGISTER_NODE.description\",\"value\":\"Register node\"},{\"key\":\"grantedClientScopes\",\"value\":\"Granted client scopes\"},{\"key\":\"clientProfileName\",\"value\":\"Client profile name\"},{\"key\":\"effectiveProtocolMappers\",\"value\":\"Effective protocol mappers\"},{\"key\":\"syncModes.legacy\",\"value\":\"Legacy\"},{\"key\":\"allowRegexComparisonHelp\",\"value\":\"If OFF, then the Subject DN from given client certificate must exactly match the given DN from the 'Subject DN' property as described in the RFC8705 specification. The Subject DN can be in the RFC4514 or RFC1779 format. If ON, then the Subject DN from given client certificate should match regex specified by 'Subject DN' property.\"},{\"key\":\"titleEvents\",\"value\":\"Events\"},{\"key\":\"signServiceProviderMetadata\",\"value\":\"Sign service provider metadata\"},{\"key\":\"attributeDefaultValue\",\"value\":\"Attribute default value\"},{\"key\":\"requestObjectEncodingHelp\",\"value\":\"JWE algorithm, which client needs to use when encrypting the content of the OIDC request object specified by 'request' or 'request_uri' parameters. If set to 'any', any algorithm is allowed.\"},{\"key\":\"minimumQuickLoginWaitSeconds\",\"value\":\"Minimum quick login wait\"},{\"key\":\"duplicate\",\"value\":\"Duplicate\"},{\"key\":\"createClientProfileNameHelperText\",\"value\":\"The name must be unique within the realm\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REGISTER_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Register error\"},{\"key\":\"selectAccountTheme\",\"value\":\"Select account theme\"},{\"key\":\"next\",\"value\":\"Next\"},{\"key\":\"import\",\"value\":\"Import\"},{\"key\":\"spinnerLoading\",\"value\":\"Loading\"},{\"key\":\"generatedUserInfoNo\",\"value\":\"No generated user info\"},{\"key\":\"allowed-client-scopes.label\",\"value\":\"Allowed Client Scopes\"},{\"key\":\"savePasswordSuccess\",\"value\":\"The password has been set successfully.\"},{\"key\":\"newRoleName\",\"value\":\"New role name\"},{\"key\":\"emailVerificationHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies independent timeout for email verification.\"},{\"key\":\"emptyInstructions\",\"value\":\"Change your search criteria or add a user\"},{\"key\":\"renameAGroup\",\"value\":\"Rename group\"},{\"key\":\"alwaysDisplayInUI\",\"value\":\"Always display in UI\"},{\"key\":\"requiredSettings\",\"value\":\"Required Settings\"},{\"key\":\"useRefreshTokens\",\"value\":\"Use refresh tokens\"},{\"key\":\"standardFlowHelp\",\"value\":\"This enables standard OpenID Connect redirect based authentication with authorization code. In terms of OpenID Connect or OAuth2 specifications, this enables support of 'Authorization Code Flow' for this client.\"},{\"key\":\"clientDeleteConfirm\",\"value\":\"If you delete this client, all associated data will be removed.\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.users.view-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if an administrator can view all users in realm\"},{\"key\":\"selectClients\",\"value\":\"Select clients\"},{\"key\":\"notBeforeClearedSuccess\",\"value\":\"Success! \\\"Not Before\\\" cleared for realm.\"},{\"key\":\"issuer\",\"value\":\"Issuer\"},{\"key\":\"policyEnforcementModeHelp\",\"value\":\"The policy enforcement mode dictates how policies are enforced when evaluating authorization requests. 'Enforcing' means requests are denied by default even when there is no policy associated with a given resource. 'Permissive' means requests are allowed even when there is no policy associated with a given resource. 'Disabled' completely disables the evaluation of policies and allows access to any resource.\"},{\"key\":\"groupCreated\",\"value\":\"Group created\"},{\"key\":\"generateError\",\"value\":\"Could not generate new key pair and certificate {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"importConfigHelp\",\"value\":\"Import metadata from a downloaded IDP discovery descriptor.\"},{\"key\":\"accessSettings\",\"value\":\"Access settings\"},{\"key\":\"emptyUserEvents\",\"value\":\"No user events\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPoliciesHelp.notEmail\",\"value\":\"The password cannot match the email address of the user.\"},{\"key\":\"deleteAttributeGroupError\",\"value\":\"Could not delete user attributes group: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"ldapErrorValidatePasswordPolicyAvailableForWritableOnly\",\"value\":\"Validate Password Policy is applicable only with WRITABLE edit mode\"},{\"key\":\"deleteValidatorConfirmTitle\",\"value\":\"Delete validator?\"},{\"key\":\"claimJsonType\",\"value\":\"JSON type that should be used to populate the json claim in the token. long, int, boolean, String and JSON are valid values.\"},{\"key\":\"kc.client.network.ip_address\",\"value\":\"Client IPv4 Address\"},{\"key\":\"signatureAndEncryption\",\"value\":\"Signature and Encryption\"},{\"key\":\"browse\",\"value\":\"Browse\"},{\"key\":\"testConnectionSuccess\",\"value\":\"Success! SMTP connection successful. E-mail was sent!\"},{\"key\":\"forgotPassword\",\"value\":\"Forgot password\"},{\"key\":\"searchUserByAttributeMissingValueError\",\"value\":\"Specify a attribute value\"},{\"key\":\"moveGroupError\",\"value\":\"Could not move group {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"clientImportSuccess\",\"value\":\"Client imported successfully\"},{\"key\":\"logicHelp\",\"value\":\"The logic dictates how the policy decision should be made. If 'Positive', the resulting effect (permit or deny) obtained during the evaluation of this policy will be used to perform a decision. If 'Negative', the resulting effect will be negated, in other words, a permit becomes a deny and vice-versa.\"},{\"key\":\"startTime\",\"value\":\"Start time\"},{\"key\":\"realmExplain\",\"value\":\"A realm manages a set of users, credentials, roles, and groups. A user belongs to and logs into a realm. Realms are isolated from one another and can only manage and authenticate the users that they control.\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnPolicyExtraOrigins\",\"value\":\"Extra Origins\"},{\"key\":\"noRolesInstructions-groups\",\"value\":\"You haven't created any roles for this group. Create a role to get started.\"},{\"key\":\"evaluateError\",\"value\":\"Could not evaluate due to: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"iconUriHelp\",\"value\":\"A URI pointing to an icon.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.OAUTH2_DEVICE_VERIFY_USER_CODE.name\",\"value\":\"OAuth2 device verify user code\"},{\"key\":\"protocol\",\"value\":\"Protocol\"},{\"key\":\"deletePermission\",\"value\":\"Permanently delete permission?\"},{\"key\":\"unLinkSuccessful\",\"value\":\"Identity provider has been unlinked\"},{\"key\":\"userFederationExplain\",\"value\":\"User federation provides access to external databases and directories, such as LDAP and Active Directory.\"},{\"key\":\"noDefaultGroups\",\"value\":\"No default groups\"},{\"key\":\"policyProvider.time\",\"value\":\"Define time conditions for your permissions.\"},{\"key\":\"updateFlowError\",\"value\":\"Could not update flow: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"selectIdentityProvider\",\"value\":\"Select an identity provider\"},{\"key\":\"nameIdPolicyFormatHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies the URI reference corresponding to a name identifier format.\"},{\"key\":\"deleteRealm\",\"value\":\"Delete realm\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_POST_LOGIN.description\",\"value\":\"Identity provider post login\"},{\"key\":\"regexAttributeValuesHelp\",\"value\":\"If enabled attribute values are interpreted as regular expressions.\"},{\"key\":\"userCreated\",\"value\":\"The user has been created\"},{\"key\":\"residentKey.not specified\",\"value\":\"Not specified\"},{\"key\":\"disableUserInfoHelp\",\"value\":\"Disable usage of User Info service to obtain additional user information?  Default is to use this OIDC service.\"},{\"key\":\"copyError\",\"value\":\"Error copying authorization details: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"frontchannelUrlInvalid\",\"value\":\"Front-channel logout URL is not a valid URL\"},{\"key\":\"deletePolicyWarning\",\"value\":\"The aggregated polices below will be removed automatically:\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_INFO_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Client info error\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.OAUTH2_DEVICE_VERIFY_USER_CODE.description\",\"value\":\"OAuth2 device verify user code\"},{\"key\":\"selectEventsListeners\",\"value\":\"Select events listeners\"},{\"key\":\"validateUuidLDAPAttribute\",\"value\":\"You must enter a UUID LDAP attribute\"},{\"key\":\"createResourceBasedPermission\",\"value\":\"Create resource-based permission\"},{\"key\":\"debugHelp\",\"value\":\"Enable/disable debug logging to standard output for Krb5LoginModule.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_FIRST_LOGIN.description\",\"value\":\"Identity provider first login\"},{\"key\":\"quickLoginCheckMilliSeconds\",\"value\":\"Quick login check milliseconds\"},{\"key\":\"whatIsDefaultGroups\",\"value\":\"What is the function of default groups?\"},{\"key\":\"generalSettings\",\"value\":\"General settings\"},{\"key\":\"requiredUserActionsHelp\",\"value\":\"Require an action when the user logs in. 'Verify email' sends an email to the user to verify their email address. 'Update profile' requires user to enter in new personal information. 'Update password' requires user to enter in a new password. 'Configure OTP' requires setup of a mobile password generator.\"},{\"key\":\"clientSecretError\",\"value\":\"Could not regenerate client secret due to: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"resourcePath\",\"value\":\"Resource path\"},{\"key\":\"useJwksUrlHelp\",\"value\":\"If the switch is on, identity provider public keys will be downloaded from given JWKS URL. This allows great flexibility because new keys will be always re-downloaded again when identity provider generates new keypair. If the switch is off, public key (or certificate) from the Keycloak DB is used, so when the identity provider keypair changes, you always need to import the new key to the Keycloak DB as well.\"},{\"key\":\"downloadAdaptorTitle\",\"value\":\"Download adaptor configs\"},{\"key\":\"selectClientAssertionSigningAlg\",\"value\":\"Select client assertion signing algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"keysFilter.PASSIVE\",\"value\":\"Passive keys\"},{\"key\":\"revocation\",\"value\":\"Revocation\"},{\"key\":\"copyFlowSuccess\",\"value\":\"Flow successfully duplicated\"},{\"key\":\"permissionDeletedError\",\"value\":\"Could not delete permission due to {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"resourceDetailsTypeHelp\",\"value\":\"The type of this resource. It can be used to group different resource instances with the same type.\"},{\"key\":\"protocolHelp\",\"value\":\"Which SSO protocol configuration is being supplied by this client scope\"},{\"key\":\"tokenDeleteError\",\"value\":\"Could not delete initial access token: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"authenticationHelp\",\"value\":\"This defines the type of the OIDC client. When it's ON, the OIDC type is set to confidential access type. When it's OFF, it is set to public access type\"},{\"key\":\"otpPolicyPeriod\",\"value\":\"OTP Token period\"},{\"key\":\"createClientProfile\",\"value\":\"Create client profile\"},{\"key\":\"language\",\"value\":\"Language\"},{\"key\":\"cachePolicy\",\"value\":\"Cache policy\"},{\"key\":\"noCredentials\",\"value\":\"No credentials\"},{\"key\":\"clientOfflineSessionIdle\",\"value\":\"Client Offline Session Idle\"},{\"key\":\"clipboardCopyDenied\",\"value\":\"Your browser is blocking access to the clipboard.\"},{\"key\":\"Friday\",\"value\":\"Friday\"},{\"key\":\"requiredForLabel.both\",\"value\":\"Both users and admins\"},{\"key\":\"CONFIGURE_TOTP\",\"value\":\"Configure OTP (CONFIGURE_TOTP)\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.EXECUTE_ACTIONS.description\",\"value\":\"Execute actions\"},{\"key\":\"clientUpdaterSourceRolesHelp\",\"value\":\"The condition checks the role of the entity who tries to create/update the client to determine whether the policy is applied.\"},{\"key\":\"validateName\",\"value\":\"You must enter a name\"},{\"key\":\"flowDetails\",\"value\":\"Flow details\"},{\"key\":\"never\",\"value\":\"Never\"},{\"key\":\"claimToRole\",\"value\":\"If a claim exists, grant the user the specified realm or client role.\"},{\"key\":\"backchannelLogoutRevokeOfflineSessionsHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifying whether a \\\"revoke_offline_access\\\" event is included in the Logout Token when the Backchannel Logout URL is used. Keycloak will revoke offline sessions when receiving a Logout Token with this event.\"},{\"key\":\"roleID\",\"value\":\"Role ID\"},{\"key\":\"filteredByClaim\",\"value\":\"Verify essential claim\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REMOVE_CREDENTIAL.name\",\"value\":\"Remove credential\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.GRANT_CONSENT.description\",\"value\":\"Grant consent\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.OAUTH2_DEVICE_AUTH_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"OAuth2 device authentication error\"},{\"key\":\"flow.firstBrokerLogin\",\"value\":\"First broker login flow\"},{\"key\":\"implicitFlow\",\"value\":\"Implicit flow\"},{\"key\":\"authorizationSignedResponseAlgHelp\",\"value\":\"JWA algorithm used for signing authorization response tokens when the response mode is jwt.\"},{\"key\":\"userName\",\"value\":\"Username\"},{\"key\":\"authenticatorRefConfig.value.help\",\"value\":\"Add a custom reference name for the authenticator. When this authenticator is successfully completed during an authentication flow, the Authentication Method Reference (AMR) protocol mapper will use this value to populate the amr claim of the generated tokens. Note, the AMR protocol must be configured for the given client to populate the AMR claim\"},{\"key\":\"clientDeleteError\",\"value\":\"Could not delete client: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"temporaryLocked\",\"value\":\"Temporarily locked\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPoliciesHelp.maxAuthAge\",\"value\":\"The maximum age of an authentication with which a password may be changed without re-authentication.\"},{\"key\":\"organizationSaveError\",\"value\":\"Could not save the organization: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"useLowerCaseBearerTypeHelp\",\"value\":\"If this is on, token responses will be set the with the type \\\"bearer\\\" in lower-case. By default, the server sets the type as \\\"Bearer\\\" as defined by RFC6750.\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConditionError\",\"value\":\"Failed to delete condition: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REFRESH_TOKEN.description\",\"value\":\"Refresh token\"},{\"key\":\"authorization\",\"value\":\"Authorization\"},{\"key\":\"invalidPasswordGenericMessage\",\"value\":\"Invalid password: new password does not match password policies.\"},{\"key\":\"userSessionAttributeValue\",\"value\":\"User Session Attribute Value\"},{\"key\":\"id\",\"value\":\"ID\"},{\"key\":\"multivalued.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Indicates if attribute supports multiple values. If true, the list of all values of this attribute will be set as claim. If false, just first value will be set as claim\"},{\"key\":\"nameHintHelp\",\"value\":\"A unique name for the group. This name will be used to reference the group when binding an attribute to a group.\"},{\"key\":\"usersPermissionsHint\",\"value\":\"Fine grained permissions for managing all users in realm.  You can define different policies for who is allowed to manage users in the realm.\"},{\"key\":\"updateResourceSuccess\",\"value\":\"Resource successfully updated\"},{\"key\":\"bruteForceStrategy.LINEAR\",\"value\":\"Linear\"},{\"key\":\"clientUpdaterSourceGroups\",\"value\":\"Groups\"},{\"key\":\"maxDeltaTimeSeconds\",\"value\":\"Failure reset time\"},{\"key\":\"infoEnabledFeatures\",\"value\":\"Shows enabled preview and experimental features.\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPoliciesHelp.lowerCase\",\"value\":\"The number of lowercase letters required in the password string.\"},{\"key\":\"maxDeltaTimeSecondsHelp\",\"value\":\"When will failure count be reset?\"},{\"key\":\"client-uris-must-match.tooltip\",\"value\":\"If on, all Client URIs (Redirect URIs and others) are allowed just if they match some trusted host or domain.\"},{\"key\":\"addIdentityProvider\",\"value\":\"Add {{provider}} provider\"},{\"key\":\"accessTokenLifespanImplicitFlow\",\"value\":\"Access Token Lifespan For Implicit Flow\"},{\"key\":\"authScopes\",\"value\":\"Authorization scopes\"},{\"key\":\"updatePasswordPolicyError\",\"value\":\"Could not update the password policies: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"mappingDetails\",\"value\":\"Mapper details\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.GRANT_CONSENT_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Grant consent error\"},{\"key\":\"hardcodedAttribute\",\"value\":\"When user is imported from provider, hardcode a value to a specific user attribute.\"},{\"key\":\"ms\",\"value\":\"milliseconds\"},{\"key\":\"keyID\",\"value\":\"KEY_ID\"},{\"key\":\"emptyValidators\",\"value\":\"No validators.\"},{\"key\":\"plus\",\"value\":\"Plus\"},{\"key\":\"anyScope\",\"value\":\"Any scope\"},{\"key\":\"enableDisable\",\"value\":\"Disabled clients cannot initiate a login or have obtained access tokens.\"},{\"key\":\"chooseAPolicyTypeInstructions\",\"value\":\"Choose one policy type from the list below and then you can configure a new policy for authorization. There are some types and description.\"},{\"key\":\"principalTypeHelp\",\"value\":\"Way to identify and track external users from the assertion. Default is using Subject NameID, alternatively you can set up identifying attribute.\"},{\"key\":\"loa-condition-level\",\"value\":\"Level of Authentication (LoA)\"},{\"key\":\"authDetails\",\"value\":\"Authorization details\"},{\"key\":\"policyEnforcementModes.DISABLED\",\"value\":\"Disabled\"},{\"key\":\"no\",\"value\":\"No\"},{\"key\":\"signatureKeyName\",\"value\":\"SAML signature key name\"},{\"key\":\"whoWillAppearPopoverFooterText\",\"value\":\"Users who have this role as an effective role cannot be added on this tab.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.RESTART_AUTHENTICATION_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Restart authentication error\"},{\"key\":\"prompts.consent\",\"value\":\"Consent\"},{\"key\":\"lastEvaluation\",\"value\":\"Last Evaluation\"},{\"key\":\"serverPrincipalHelp\",\"value\":\"Full name of server principal for HTTP service including server and domain name. For example, HTTP/host.foo.org@FOO.ORG\"},{\"key\":\"on\",\"value\":\"On\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.OAUTH2_DEVICE_AUTH.name\",\"value\":\"OAuth2 device authentication\"},{\"key\":\"or\",\"value\":\"or\"},{\"key\":\"includeInLightweight.label\",\"value\":\"Add to lightweight access token\"},{\"key\":\"AESKeySizeHelp\",\"value\":\"Size in bytes for the generated AES key. Size 16 is for AES-128, Size 24 for AES-192, and Size 32 for AES-256. WARN: Bigger keys than 128 are not allowed on some JDK implementations.\"},{\"key\":\"emptyMembersInstructions\",\"value\":\"There are no members yet. Please add them to this organization\"},{\"key\":\"rowEditBtnAriaLabel\",\"value\":\"Edit {{messageBundle}}\"},{\"key\":\"addDefaultGroups\",\"value\":\"Add default groups\"},{\"key\":\"deleteCredentialsSuccess\",\"value\":\"The credentials has been deleted successfully.\"},{\"key\":\"addAttributeDisplayDescriptionTranslation\",\"value\":\"Add translation for the display description\"},{\"key\":\"unsavedChangesTitle\",\"value\":\"Unsaved changes\"},{\"key\":\"noSearchResults\",\"value\":\"No search results\"},{\"key\":\"readBlog\",\"value\":\"Read blog\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.AUTHREQID_TO_TOKEN.description\",\"value\":\"Authreqid to token\"},{\"key\":\"recent\",\"value\":\"Recent\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.USER_INFO_REQUEST.description\",\"value\":\"User info request\"},{\"key\":\"client-updater-trusted-hosts.tooltip\",\"value\":\"List of Hosts, which are trusted. In case that client registration/update request comes from the host/domain specified in this configuration, condition evaluates to true. You can use hostnames or IP addresses. If you use star at the beginning (for example '*.example.com' ) then whole domain example.com will be trusted.\"},{\"key\":\"noResourceCreateHint\",\"value\":\"There are no resources you can't create resource-based permission\"},{\"key\":\"directMembership\",\"value\":\"Direct membership\"},{\"key\":\"associatedRolesText\",\"value\":\"Associated roles\"},{\"key\":\"ldapConnectionAndAuthorizationSettingsDescription\",\"value\":\"This section contains options related to the configuration of the connection to the LDAP server. It also contains options related to authentication of the LDAP connection to the LDAP server.\"},{\"key\":\"flow-type.basic-flow\",\"value\":\"Generic\"},{\"key\":\"deletedSuccessRealmSetting\",\"value\":\"The realm has been deleted\"},{\"key\":\"webauthnPasswordlessPolicy\",\"value\":\"Webauthn Passwordless Policy\"},{\"key\":\"editUserLabel\",\"value\":\"Edit User Label Button\"},{\"key\":\"resourceSaveError\",\"value\":\"Could not persist resource due to {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"chooseBindingType\",\"value\":\"Choose binding type\"},{\"key\":\"itemDelete\",\"value\":\"Delete item\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientPolicyProfileConfirmTitle\",\"value\":\"Delete profile?\"},{\"key\":\"noRolesInstructions-users\",\"value\":\"You haven't assigned any roles to this user. Assign a role to get started.\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPoliciesHelp.upperCase\",\"value\":\"The number of uppercase letters required in the password string.\"},{\"key\":\"email\",\"value\":\"Email\"},{\"key\":\"started\",\"value\":\"Started\"},{\"key\":\"mapperTypeCertificateLdapMapperHelp\",\"value\":\"Used to map single attribute which contains a certificate from LDAP user to attribute of UserModel in Keycloak DB\"},{\"key\":\"addAttribute\",\"value\":\"Add {{label}}\"},{\"key\":\"to\",\"value\":\"the attribute. For that, make sure to use any of the built-in validators to properly validate the size and the values.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.FEDERATED_IDENTITY_OVERRIDE_LINK_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Federated identity link override error\"},{\"key\":\"updatePolicySuccess\",\"value\":\"Successfully updated the policy\"},{\"key\":\"updateExecutorError\",\"value\":\"Executor not updated: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"createdAt\",\"value\":\"Created at\"},{\"key\":\"clientOfflineSessionMaxHelp\",\"value\":\"Max time before a client offline session is expired. If Offline Session Max Limited is enabled at realm level, offline tokens are invalidated when a client offline session is expired. The option does not affect the global user SSO session. If not set, it uses the realm Offline Session Max value.\"},{\"key\":\"strictTransportSecurity\",\"value\":\"HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS)\"},{\"key\":\"offlineSessionMaxLimited\",\"value\":\"Offline Session Max Limited\"},{\"key\":\"providerCreateSuccess\",\"value\":\"New client policy created successfully\"},{\"key\":\"jwtX509HeadersEnabledHelp\",\"value\":\"If enabled, the x5t (X.509 Certificate SHA-1 Thumbprint) header will be added to the JWT to reference the certificate used to sign it. Otherwise, the kid (Key ID) header will be used instead.\"},{\"key\":\"defaultGroupAdded_one\",\"value\":\"New group added to the default groups\"},{\"key\":\"unexpectedError\",\"value\":\"An unexpected error occurred: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"preview\",\"value\":\"Preview\"},{\"key\":\"permissionDeletedSuccess\",\"value\":\"Successfully deleted permission\"},{\"key\":\"previous\",\"value\":\"Previous\"},{\"key\":\"compositesRemovedAlertDescription\",\"value\":\"All the associated roles have been removed\"},{\"key\":\"javaKeystore\",\"value\":\"java-keystore\"},{\"