 used in most of the requests sent to the LDAP server. Currently only 'none' (anonymous LDAP authentication) or 'simple' (bind credential + bind password authentication) mechanisms are available.\"},{\"key\":\"whoWillAppearPopoverText\",\"value\":\"Groups are hierarchical. When you select Direct Membership, you see only the child group that the user joined. Ancestor groups are not included.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VERIFY_EMAIL.description\",\"value\":\"Verify email\"},{\"key\":\"validatingPublicKeyIdHelp\",\"value\":\"Explicit ID of the validating public key given above if the key ID. Leave blank if the key above should be used always, regardless of key ID specified by external IDP; set it if the key should only be used for verifying if the key ID from external IDP matches.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_LINK_ACCOUNT_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Identity provider link account error\"},{\"key\":\"effectiveRoleScopeMappingsHelp\",\"value\":\"Selected Optional Client Scopes, which will be used when issuing access token for this client. You can see above what value of OAuth Scope Parameter needs to be used when you want to have these optional client scopes applied when the initial OpenID Connect Authentication request will be sent from your client adapter\"},{\"key\":\"userDeletedSuccess\",\"value\":\"The user has been deleted\"},{\"key\":\"contentSecurityPolicyReportOnlyHelp\",\"value\":\"For testing Content Security Policies <1>Learn more</1>\"},{\"key\":\"topLevelFlowTypeHelp\",\"value\":\"What kind of top level flow is it? Type 'client' is used for authentication of clients (applications) when generic is for users and everything else\"},{\"key\":\"policyProvider.regex\",\"value\":\"Define regex conditions for your permissions.\"},{\"key\":\"clientImportError\",\"value\":\"Could not import client: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"artifactResolutionServiceUrl\",\"value\":\"Artifact Resolution service URL\"},{\"key\":\"comparison\",\"value\":\"Comparison\"},{\"key\":\"