 Max\\\" time defined at realm level.\"},{\"key\":\"lastRegistration\",\"value\":\"Last registration\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REMOVE_CREDENTIAL_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Remove credential error\"},{\"key\":\"noKeys\",\"value\":\"No keys\"},{\"key\":\"kerberosKeyTab\",\"value\":\"Kerberos Key Tab\"},{\"key\":\"principalAttribute\",\"value\":\"Principal attribute\"},{\"key\":\"userRegistrationHelpText\",\"value\":\"Enable/disable the registration page. A link for registration will show on login page too.\"},{\"key\":\"fineGrainOpenIdConnectConfigurationHelp\",\"value\":\"This section is used to configure advanced settings of this client related to OpenID Connect protocol.\"},{\"key\":\"addTranslationDialogOkBtn\",\"value\":\"Ok\"},{\"key\":\"setToNowError\",\"value\":\"Error! Failed to set notBefore to current date and time: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.SEND_VERIFY_EMAIL_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Send verify email error\"},{\"key\":\"roleObjectClasses\",\"value\":\"Role object classes\"},{\"key\":\"groupDuplicated\",\"value\":\"Group duplicated\"},{\"key\":\"clientUpdaterTrustedHostsTooltip\",\"value\":\"List of Hosts, which are trusted. In case that client registration/update request comes from the host/domain specified in this configuration, condition evaluates to true. You can use hostnames or IP addresses. If you use star at the beginning (for example '*.example.com' ) then whole domain example.com will be trusted.\"},{\"key\":\"titleRoles\",\"value\":\"Realm roles\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REVOKE_GRANT.name\",\"value\":\"Revoke grant\"},{\"key\":\"addAttributeTranslationBtn\",\"value\":\"Add translation button\"},{\"key\":\"noItems\",\"value\":\"There are no items\"},{\"key\":\"syncModeHelp\",\"value\":\"Default sync mode for all mappers. The sync mode determines when user data will be synced using the mappers. Possible values are: 'legacy' to keep the behaviour before this option was introduced, 'import' to only import the user once during first login of the user with this identity provider, 'force' to always update the user during every login with this identity provider.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.OAUTH2_DEVICE_VERIFY_USER_CODE_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"OAuth2 device verify user code error\"},{\"key\":\"xContentTypeOptionsHelp\",\"value\":\"Default value prevents Internet Explorer and Google Chrome from MIME-sniffing a response away from the declared content-type <1>Learn more</1>\"},{\"key\":\"privateKeyMask\",\"value\":\"PRIVATE KEY NOT SET UP OR KNOWN\"},{\"key\":\"addExecutorSuccess\",\"value\":\"Success! Executor created successfully\"},{\"key\":\"learnMore\",\"value\":\"Learn more\"},{\"key\":\"onDragCancel\",\"value\":\"Dragging cancelled. List is unchanged.\"},{\"key\":\"offlineSessionSettings\",\"value\":\"Offline session settings\"},{\"key\":\"deleteScope\",\"value\":\"Permanently delete authorization scope?\"},{\"key\":\"clientPolicies\",\"value\":\"Client policies\"},{\"key\":\"NONE\",\"value\":\"NONE\"},{\"key\":\"keystorePasswordHelp\",\"value\":\"Password for the keys\"},{\"key\":\"createRealm\",\"value\":\"Create realm\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_LOGIN_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Client login error\"},{\"key\":\"displayOnConsentScreenHelp\",\"value\":\"If on, and this client scope is added to some client with consent required, the text specified by 'Consent Screen Text' will be displayed on consent screen. If off, this client scope will not be displayed on the consent screen\"},{\"key\":\"titleUsers\",\"value\":\"Users\"},{\"key\":\"whoWillAppearLinkText\",\"value\":\"Who will appear in this group list?\"},{\"key\":\"noRoles-clients\",\"value\":\"No roles for this client scope\"},{\"key\":\"forceAuthenticationHelp\",\"value\":\"Indicates whether the identity provider must authenticate the presenter directly rather than rely on a previous security context.\"},{\"key\":\"reGenerateSigning\",\"value\":\"Regenerate signing key for this client\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmGroup_other\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to delete these groups.\"},{\"key\":\"userAddedOrganization_other\",\"value\":\"{{count}} organizations added to the user\"},{\"key\":\"allResults\",\"value\":\"All results\"},{\"key\":\"invalidEmailMessage\",\"value\":\"'{{0}}': Invalid email address.\"},{\"key\":\"keyForCodeExchangeHelp\",\"value\":\"Choose which code challenge method for PKCE is used. If not specified, keycloak does not applies PKCE to a client unless the client sends an authorization request with appropriate code challenge and code exchange method.\"},{\"key\":\"removeMappingConfirm_one\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to remove this role?\"},{\"key\":\"orderChangeSuccessUserFed\",\"value\":\"Successfully changed the priority order of user federation providers\"},{\"key\":\"noUsersEmptyStateDescriptionContinued\",\"value\":\"to find them. Users that already have this role as an effective role cannot be added here.\"},{\"key\":\"executorsHelpText\",\"value\":\"Executors, which will be applied for this client profile\"},{\"key\":\"supportJwtClaimInIntrospectionResponse\",\"value\":\"Support JWT claim in Introspection Response\"},{\"key\":\"caseSensitiveOriginalUsernameHelp\",\"value\":\"If enabled, the original username from the identity provider is kept as is when federating users. Otherwise, the username from the identity provider is lower-cased and might not match the original value if it is case-sensitive. This setting only affects the username associated with the federated identity as usernames in the server are always in lower-case.\"},{\"key\":\"ldapSearchingAndUpdatingSettings\",\"value\":\"LDAP searching and updating\"},{\"key\":\"passLoginHintHelp\",\"value\":\"Pass login_hint to identity provider.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_LOGIN.description\",\"value\":\"Client login\"},{\"key\":\"issuerHelp\",\"value\":\"The issuer identifier for the issuer of the response. If not provided, no validation will be performed.\"},{\"key\":\"titleSessions\",\"value\":\"Sessions\"},{\"key\":\"dedicatedScopeName\",\"value\":\"{{clientName}}-dedicated\"},{\"key\":\"policyUsers\",\"value\":\"Specifies which user(s) are allowed by this policy.\"},{\"key\":\"logoutServicePostBindingURLHelp\",\"value\":\"SAML POST Binding URL for the client's single logout service. You can leave this blank if you are using a different binding\"},{\"key\":\"realmNameField\",\"value\":\"Realm name\"},{\"key\":\"roleCreated\",\"value\":\"Role created\"},{\"key\":\"noViewRights\",\"value\":\"You do not have rights to view this group.\"},{\"key\":\"resourceScopeError\",\"value\":\"Could not remove the authorization scope due to {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"identityInformation\",\"value\":\"Identity Information\"},{\"key\":\"usermodel.clientRoleMapping.rolePrefix.label\",\"value\":\"Client Role prefix\"},{\"key\":\"decisionStrategyHelp\",\"value\":\"The decision strategy dictates how permissions are evaluated and how a final decision is obtained. 'Affirmative' means that at least one permission must evaluate to a positive decision in order to grant access to a resource and its scopes. 'Unanimous' means that all permissions must evaluate to a positive decision in order for the final decision to be also positive.\"},{\"key\":\"hideOnLoginPage\",\"value\":\"Hide on login page\"},{\"key\":\"defaultRole\",\"value\":\"This role serves as a container for both realm and client default roles. It cannot be removed.\"},{\"key\":\"eventConfigs\",\"value\":\"Event configs\"},{\"key\":\"orderChangeSuccess\",\"value\":\"Successfully changed display order of identity providers\"},{\"key\":\"accessTokenLifespanImplicitFlowHelp\",\"value\":\"Max time before an access token issued during OpenID Connect Implicit Flow is expired. This value is recommended to be shorter than the SSO timeout. There is no possibility to refresh token during implicit flow, that's why there is a separate timeout different to 'Access Token Lifespan'\"},{\"key\":\"usernameLdapAttributeHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of the LDAP attribute, which is mapped as Keycloak username. For many LDAP server vendors it can be 'uid'. For Active directory it can be 'sAMAccountName' or 'cn'. The attribute should be filled for all LDAP user records you want to import from LDAP to Keycloak.\"},{\"key\":\"storedTokensReadable\",\"value\":\"Stored tokens readable\"},{\"key\":\"unlinkUsersError\",\"value\":\"Could not unlink users: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"ldapErrorCantWriteOnlyForReadOnlyLdap\",\"value\":\"Can not set write only when LDAP provider mode is not WRITABLE\"},{\"key\":\"deleteAttributeSuccess\",\"value\":\"Attribute deleted\"},{\"key\":\"error-invalid-length\",\"value\":\"'{{0}}' must have a length between {{1}} and {{2}}.\"},{\"key\":\"mapperTypeMsadLdsUserAccountControlMapper\",\"value\":\"msad-user-account-control-mapper\"},{\"key\":\"scopeDisplayNameHelp\",\"value\":\"A unique name for this scope. The name can be used to uniquely identify a scope, useful when querying for a specific scope.\"},{\"key\":\"executorTypeSelectAlgorithm\",\"value\":\"Executor Type Select Algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"importKey\",\"value\":\"Import key\"},{\"key\":\"forceArtifactBindingHelp\",\"value\":\"Should response messages be returned to the client through the SAML ARTIFACT binding system?\"},{\"key\":\"forceAuthentication\",\"value\":\"Force authentication\"},{\"key\":\"deletePolicy\",\"value\":\"Permanently delete policy?\"},{\"key\":\"assertionConsumerServiceRedirectBindingURLHelp\",\"value\":\"SAML Redirect Binding URL for the client's assertion consumer service (login responses). You can leave this blank if you do not have a URL for this binding.\"},{\"key\":\"providers\",\"value\":\"Add providers\"},{\"key\":\"customAttribute\",\"value\":\"Custom AttributeŌĆ”\"},{\"key\":\"addClientScope\",\"value\":\"Add client scope\"},{\"key\":\"syncRegistrations\",\"value\":\"Sync Registrations\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_REGISTER_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Client register error\"},{\"key\":\"unlockUsersError\",\"value\":\"Could not unlock all users {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_CONSENT_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Update consent error\"},{\"key\":\"noAdminUrlSet\",\"value\":\"No push sent. No admin URI configured or no registered cluster nodes available\"},{\"key\":\"chooseAPolicyType\",\"value\":\"Choose a policy type\"},{\"key\":\"UPDATE_PASSWORD\",\"value\":\"Update password (UPDATE_PASSWORD)\"},{\"key\":\"certificateHelp\",\"value\":\"Client Certificate for validate JWT issued by client and signed by Client private key from your keystore.\"},{\"key\":\"showMore\",\"value\":\"Show more\"},{\"key\":\"generalOptions\",\"value\":\"General options\"},{\"key\":\"userLdapFilterHelp\",\"value\":\"Additional LDAP filter for filtering searched users. Leave this empty if you don't need an additional filter. Make sure that it starts with '(' and ends with ')'.\"},{\"key\":\"realmOverridesDescription\",\"value\":\"Realm overrides allow you to specify translations that will take effect for the entire realm. These translations will override any translation specified by a theme.\"},{\"key\":\"clientAuthenticator\",\"value\":\"Client Authenticator\"},{\"key\":\"importAdded_other\",\"value\":\"{{count}} records added.\"},{\"key\":\"deleteGroup\",\"value\":\"Delete group\"},{\"key\":\"clientSessionMax\",\"value\":\"Client Session Max\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientPolicy\",\"value\":\"Delete client policy\"},{\"key\":\"writableSelection\",\"value\":\"Writable selection\"},{\"key\":\"clientAuthentications.private_key_jwt\",\"value\":\"JWT signed with private key\"},{\"key\":\"createClientSuccess\",\"value\":\"Client created successfully\"},{\"key\":\"editCondition\",\"value\":\"Edit condition\"},{\"key\":\"ssoSessionMaxRememberMe\",\"value\":\"Max time before a session is expired when a user has set the remember me option. Tokens and browser sessions are invalidated when a session is expired. If not set it uses the standard SSO Session Max value.\"},{\"key\":\"exportFail\",\"value\":\"Could not export realm: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"flowTypeHelp\",\"value\":\"What kind of form is it\"},{\"key\":\"setPasswordConfirm\",\"value\":\"Set password?\"},{\"key\":\"attributeDisplayNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Display name for the attribute. Supports keys for localized values as well. For example: ${profile.attribute.phoneNumber}. Hit the 'Globe Route' icon to add translations.\"},{\"key\":\"assignedType\",\"value\":\"Assigned type\"},{\"key\":\"modeHelp\",\"value\":\"LDAP_ONLY means that all group mappings of users are retrieved from LDAP and saved into LDAP. READ_ONLY is Read-only LDAP mode where group mappings are retrieved from both LDAP and DB and merged together. New group joins are not saved to LDAP but to DB. IMPORT is Read-only LDAP mode where group mappings are retrieved from LDAP just at the time when user is imported from LDAP and then they are saved to local keycloak DB.\"},{\"key\":\"identityProvider\",\"value\":\"Identity provider\"},{\"key\":\"mapperTypeMsadLdsUserAccountControlMapperHelp\",\"value\":\"Mapper specific to MSAD LDS. It's able to integrate the MSAD LDS user account state into Keycloak account state (account enabled, password is expired etc). It's using msDS-UserAccountDisabled and pwdLastSet is 0, the Keycloak user is required to update password, if msDS-UserAccountDisabled is 'TRUE' the Keycloak user is disabled as well etc. Mapper is also able to handle exception code from LDAP user authentication.\"},{\"key\":\"validations\",\"value\":\"Validations\"},{\"key\":\"updatedRequiredActionError\",\"value\":\"Could not update required action: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"createChildGroup\",\"value\":\"Create child group\"},{\"key\":\"x509Certificate\",\"value\":\"X509 Certificate\"},{\"key\":\"createPolicySuccess\",\"value\":\"Successfully created the policy\"},{\"key\":\"openIDEndpointConfiguration\",\"value\":\"OpenID Endpoint Configuration\"},{\"key\":\"prompts.login\",\"value\":\"Login\"},{\"key\":\"keyTabHelp\",\"value\":\"Location of Kerberos KeyTab file containing the credentials of server principal. For example, /etc/krb5.keytab\"},{\"key\":\"wantAssertionsEncrypted\",\"value\":\"Want Assertions encrypted\"},{\"key\":\"uris\",\"value\":\"URIs\"},{\"key\":\"validateKeyTab\",\"value\":\"You must enter a key tab\"},{\"key\":\"editUsernameAllowed\",\"value\":\"Edit username\"},{\"key\":\"searchForPermission\",\"value\":\"Search for permission\"},{\"key\":\"clientUpdaterSourceGroupsTooltip\",\"value\":\"Name of groups to check. Condition evaluates to true if the entity, who creates/updates client is member of some of the specified groups. Configured groups are specified by their simple name, which must match to the name of the Keycloak group. No support for group hierarchy is used here.\"},{\"key\":\"ldapAttributeValue\",\"value\":\"LDAP attribute value\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_DELETE.description\",\"value\":\"Client delete\"},{\"key\":\"roleHelp\",\"value\":\"Role to grant to user if all attributes are present. Click 'Select Role' button to browse roles, or just type it in the textbox. To reference a client role the syntax is clientname.clientrole, i.e. myclient.myrole\"},{\"key\":\"registrationAllowed\",\"value\":\"User registration\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.TOKEN_EXCHANGE.name\",\"value\":\"Token exchange\"},{\"key\":\"searchForClientScope\",\"value\":\"Search for client scope\"},{\"key\":\"userCache\",\"value\":\"User Cache\"},{\"key\":\"selectLanguage\",\"value\":\"Select language\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.USER_INFO_REQUEST_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"User info request error\"},{\"key\":\"policyRoles\",\"value\":\"Specifies the client roles allowed by this policy.\"},{\"key\":\"refreshTokenMaxReuseHelp\",\"value\":\"Maximum number of times a refresh token can be reused. When a different token is used, revocation is immediate.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REMOVE_FEDERATED_IDENTITY.description\",\"value\":\"Remove federated identity\"},{\"key\":\"bruteForceMode\",\"value\":\"Brute Force Mode\"},{\"key\":\"childGroups\",\"value\":\"Child groups\"},{\"key\":\"exportAuthDetailsError\",\"value\":\"Error exporting authorization details: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"selectGroups\",\"value\":\"Select groups to join\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnPolicyAuthenticatorAttachmentHelp\",\"value\":\"Communicates to an authenticator an acceptable attachment pattern.\"},{\"key\":\"replyToDisplayNameHelp\",\"value\":\"A user-friendly name for the 'Reply-To' address (optional).\"},{\"key\":\"signingKeysConfigExplain\",\"value\":\"If you enable the \\\"Client signature required\\\" below, you must configure the signing keys by generating or importing keys, and the client will sign their saml requests and responses. The signature will be validated.\"},{\"key\":\"identityProviderUnlink\",\"value\":\"Unlink identity provider?\"},{\"key\":\"fullScopeAllowedHelp\",\"value\":\"Allows you to disable all restrictions.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.SEND_IDENTITY_PROVIDER_LINK_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Send identity provider link error\"},{\"key\":\"groupNameLdapAttribute\",\"value\":\"Group name LDAP attribute\"},{\"key\":\"managedMembership\",\"value\":\"Managed membership\"},{\"key\":\"includeInTokenScope\",\"value\":\"Include in token scope\"},{\"key\":\"tokenDeleteConfirmTitle\",\"value\":\"Delete initial access token?\"},{\"key\":\"resetPasswordFor\",\"value\":\"Reset password for {{username}}\"},{\"key\":\"deleteEventsConfirm\",\"value\":\"If you clear all events of this realm, all records will be permanently cleared in the database\"},{\"key\":\"organizationsExplain\",\"value\":\"Manage your organizations and members.\"},{\"key\":\"groupUpdateError\",\"value\":\"Error updating group {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"rememberMeHelpText\",\"value\":\"Show checkbox on login page to allow user to remain logged in between browser restarts until session expires.\"},{\"key\":\"createFlowHelp\",\"value\":\"You can create a top level flow within this from\"},{\"key\":\"kerberos\",\"value\":\"Kerberos\"},{\"key\":\"login\",\"value\":\"Login\"},{\"key\":\"noGroupsInThisSubGroupInstructions\",\"value\":\"You haven't created any groups in this sub group.\"},{\"key\":\"policyDetails\",\"value\":\"Policy details\"},{\"key\":\"testConnectionHint.withEmail\",\"value\":\"When testing the connection an e-mail will be sent to the current user ({{email}}).\"},{\"key\":\"adminURLHelp\",\"value\":\"URL to the admin interface of the client. Set this if the client supports the adapter REST API. This REST API allows the auth server to push revocation policies and other administrative tasks. Usually this is set to the base URL of the client.\"},{\"key\":\"otpPolicyCodeReusableHelp\",\"value\":\"Possibility to use the same OTP code again after successful authentication.\"},{\"key\":\"locales\",\"value\":\"Locales\"},{\"key\":\"userFedDeletedSuccess\",\"value\":\"The user federation provider has been deleted.\"},{\"key\":\"logic\",\"value\":\"Logic\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopeSearch.type\",\"value\":\"Assigned type\"},{\"key\":\"organizationUsersAdded_one\",\"value\":\"{{count}} user added to the organization\"},{\"key\":\"linkUpdateError\",\"value\":\"Could not update link to identity provider: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"addSavedTypes\",\"value\":\"Add saved types\"},{\"key\":\"generatedAccessTokenNo\",\"value\":\"No generated access token\"},{\"key\":\"settings\",\"value\":\"Settings\"},{\"key\":\"failureFactorHelp\",\"value\":\"How many failures before wait is triggered.\"},{\"key\":\"domains\",\"value\":\"Domains\"},{\"key\":\"noSessions\",\"value\":\"No sessions\"},{\"key\":\"storeTokens\",\"value\":\"Store tokens\"},{\"key\":\"addClientScopesTo\",\"value\":\"Add client scopes to {{clientName}}\"},{\"key\":\"Sunday\",\"value\":\"Sunday\"},{\"key\":\"emptyOrganizations\",\"value\":\"No organizations\"},{\"key\":\"addAttributeDisplayNameTranslation\",\"value\":\"Add translation for the display name\"},{\"key\":\"clientUpdaterContext\",\"value\":\"The condition checks the context how is client created/updated to determine whether the policy is applied. For example it checks if client is created with admin REST API or OIDC dynamic client registration. And for the letter case if it is ANONYMOUS client registration or AUTHENTICATED client registration with Initial access token or Registration access token and so on.\"},{\"key\":\"removedGroupMembership\",\"value\":\"Removed group membership\"},{\"key\":\"compositeRoleOff\",\"value\":\"Composite role turned off\"},{\"key\":\"defaultPasswordLabel\",\"value\":\"My password\"},{\"key\":\"importClient\",\"value\":\"Import client\"},{\"key\":\"deleteMapperSuccess\",\"value\":\"Mapper successfully deleted.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_INITIATED_ACCOUNT_LINKING_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Client initiated account linking error\"},{\"key\":\"createFlow\",\"value\":\"Create flow\"},{\"key\":\"oAuthDPoPHelp\",\"value\":\"This enables support for Demonstrating Proof-of-Possession (DPoP) bound tokens. The access and refresh tokens are bound to the key stored on the user agent. In order to prove the possession of the key, the user agent must send a signed proof alongside the token.\"},{\"key\":\"membershipLdapAttributeHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of LDAP attribute on group, which is used for membership mappings. Usually it will be 'member'. However when 'Membership Attribute Type' is 'UID', then 'Membership LDAP Attribute' could be typically 'memberUid'.\"},{\"key\":\"pushedAuthorizationRequestRequiredHelp\",\"value\":\"Boolean parameter indicating whether the authorization server accepts authorization request data only via the pushed authorization request method.\"},{\"key\":\"useJwksUrl\",\"value\":\"Use JWKS URL\"},{\"key\":\"userGroupsRetrieveStrategy\",\"value\":\"User groups retrieve strategy\"},{\"key\":\"addSubFlow\",\"value\":\"Add sub-flow\"},{\"key\":\"replyToEmailPlaceholder\",\"value\":\"Reply to email address\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.roles.map-role-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if an administrator can map this role to a user or group\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.LOGIN.description\",\"value\":\"Login\"},{\"key\":\"impersonateConfirm\",\"value\":\"Impersonate user?\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.clients.map-roles-client-scope-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if an administrator can apply roles defined by this client to the client scope of another client\"},{\"key\":\"includeInIdToken.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Should the claim be added to the ID token?\"},{\"key\":\"federationLinkHelp\",\"value\":\"UserStorageProvider this locally stored user was imported from.\"},{\"key\":\"validateUsernameLDAPAttribute\",\"value\":\"You must enter a username LDAP attribute\"},{\"key\":\"waitIncrementSecondsHelp\",\"value\":\"When failure threshold has been met, how much time should the user be locked out?\"},{\"key\":\"allowedClockSkew\",\"value\":\"Allowed clock skew\"},{\"key\":\"moveToGroup\",\"value\":\"Move {{group1}} to {{group2}}\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.PUSHED_AUTHORIZATION_REQUEST.description\",\"value\":\"Pushed authorization request\"},{\"key\":\"addIdpMapperNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of the mapper.\"},{\"key\":\"claimFilterValueHelp\",\"value\":\"Value of the essential claim (with regex support)\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.groups.manage-members-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide if an administrator can manage the members of this group\"},{\"key\":\"groupName\",\"value\":\"Group name\"},{\"key\":\"emptyProfiles\",\"value\":\"No client profiles configured\"},{\"key\":\"createClientProfileError\",\"value\":\"Could not create client profile: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"searchClientAuthorizationPermission\",\"value\":\"Search permission\"},{\"key\":\"defaultLanguage\",\"value\":\"Default\"},{\"key\":\"encryption\",\"value\":\"Encryption\"},{\"key\":\"vendor\",\"value\":\"Vendor\"},{\"key\":\"disabled\",\"value\":\"Disabled\"},{\"key\":\"attribute\",\"value\":\"Attribute\"},{\"key\":\"unLinkIdentityProvider\",\"value\":\"Unlink provider\"},{\"key\":\"timestamp\",\"value\":\"Created date\"},{\"key\":\"principalAttributeHelp\",\"value\":\"Name or Friendly Name of the attribute used to identify external users.\"},{\"key\":\"idpInitiatedSsoUrlName\",\"value\":\"IDP-Initiated SSO URL name\"},{\"key\":\"selectMethod\",\"value\":\"Select method\"},{\"key\":\"xFrameOptions\",\"value\":\"X-Frame-Options\"},{\"key\":\"scopeDescriptionHelp\",\"value\":\"Description of the client scope\"},{\"key\":\"copyInitialAccessToken\",\"value\":\"Please copy and paste the initial access token before closing as it can not be retrieved later.\"},{\"key\":\"supported\",\"value\":\"Supported\"},{\"key\":\"roleImportSuccess\",\"value\":\"Role import successful\"},{\"key\":\"addAnnotationText\",\"value\":\"Add annotation\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_TOTP_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Update totp error\"},{\"key\":\"clientBaseURLInvalid\",\"value\":\"Base URL is not a valid URL\"},{\"key\":\"acceptsPromptNoneHelp\",\"value\":\"This is just used together with Identity Provider Authenticator or when kc_idp_hint points to this identity provider. In case that client sends a request with prompt=none and user is not yet authenticated, the error will not be directly returned to client, but the request with prompt=none will be forwarded to this identity provider.\"},{\"key\":\"pairwiseMalformedSectorIdentifierURI\",\"value\":\"Malformed Sector Identifier URI.\"},{\"key\":\"userRolesRetrieveStrategyHelp\",\"value\":\"Specify how to retrieve roles of user. LOAD_ROLES_BY_MEMBER_ATTRIBUTE means that roles fo user will be retrieved by sending LDAP query to retrieve all roles where 'member' is our user. GET_ROLES_FROM_USER_MEMBEROF means that roles of user will be retrieved from 'memberOf' attribute of our user. Or from the other attributes specified by 'Member-Of LDAP Attribute'. LOAD_ROLES_BY_MEMBER_ATTRIBUTE is applicable just in Active Directory and it means that roles of user will be retrieved recursively with usage of LDAP_MATCHING_RULE_IN_CHAIN LDAP extension.\"},{\"key\":\"roleDeleteError\",\"value\":\"Could not delete role: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_PASSWORD_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Update password error\"},{\"key\":\"addGroups\",\"value\":\"Add groups\"},{\"key\":\"offlineSessionIdle\",\"value\":\"Offline Session Idle\"},{\"key\":\"mapperAttributeFriendlyName\",\"value\":\"Friendly name\"},{\"key\":\"roleDeleteConfirm\",\"value\":\"Delete role?\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmDialog_other\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to permanently delete {{count}} selected users\"},{\"key\":\"changeAuthenticatorConfirm\",\"value\":\"If you change authenticator to {{clientAuthenticatorType}}, the Keycloak database will be updated and you may need to download a new adapter configuration for this client.\"},{\"key\":\"idpAccountEmailVerificationHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies independent timeout for IdP account email verification.\"},{\"key\":\"alwaysReadValueFromLdap\",\"value\":\"Always read value from LDAP\"},{\"key\":\"assignedClientScope\",\"value\":\"Assigned client scope\"},{\"key\":\"Tuesday\",\"value\":\"Tuesday\"},{\"key\":\"idTokenEncryptionContentEncryptionAlgorithm\",\"value\":\"ID token encryption content encryption algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"unmanagedAttributePolicy.ADMIN_VIEW\",\"value\":\"Only administrators can view\"},{\"key\":\"addClientProfile\",\"value\":\"Add client profile\"},{\"key\":\"eventConfigError\",\"value\":\"Could not save event configuration {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"userSaved\",\"value\":\"The user has been saved\"},{\"key\":\"derFormattedHelp\",\"value\":\"Activate this if the certificate is DER formatted in LDAP and not PEM formatted.\"},{\"key\":\"policySaveError\",\"value\":\"Could not update the policy: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"tokenLifespan.inherited\",\"value\":\"Inherits from realm settings\"},{\"key\":\"selectAUser\",\"value\":\"Select a user\"},{\"key\":\"attestationPreference.not specified\",\"value\":\"Not specified\"},{\"key\":\"updateFlowSuccess\",\"value\":\"Flow successfully updated\"},{\"key\":\"selectFlowType\",\"value\":\"Select flow type\"},{\"key\":\"trustEmail\",\"value\":\"Trust Email\"},{\"key\":\"error-number-out-of-range-too-big\",\"value\":\"'{{0}}' must have maximal value of {{2}}.\"},{\"key\":\"hardcodedUserSessionAttribute\",\"value\":\"When a user is imported from a provider, hardcode a value to a specific user session attribute.\"},{\"key\":\"organizationDomainHelp\",\"value\":\"A set of one or more internet domains associated with the organization. The domain is used to map users to an organization based on their email domain and to authenticate them accordingly in the scope of the organization.\"},{\"key\":\"usermodel.realmRoleMapping.rolePrefix.label\",\"value\":\"Realm Role prefix\"},{\"key\":\"importOverwritten_zero\",\"value\":\"No records overwritten.\"},{\"key\":\"samlSettings\",\"value\":\"SAML settings\"},{\"key\":\"userFedDisableConfirm\",\"value\":\"If you disable this user federation provider, it will not be considered for queries and imported users will be disabled and read-only until the provider is enabled again.\"},{\"key\":\"enabled\",\"value\":\"Enabled\"},{\"key\":\"noLanguages\",\"value\":\"No languages\"},{\"key\":\"lightweightAccessToken\",\"value\":\"Always use lightweight access token\"},{\"key\":\"invalidPasswordNotUsernameMessage\",\"value\":\"Invalid password: must not be equal to the username.\"},{\"key\":\"implicitFlowHelp\",\"value\":\"This enables support for OpenID Connect redirect based authentication without authorization code. In terms of OpenID Connect or OAuth2 specifications, this enables support of 'Implicit Flow' for this client.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IMPERSONATE_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Impersonate error\"},{\"key\":\"clientNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies display name of the client. For example 'My Client'. Supports keys for localized values as well. For example: ${my_client}\"},{\"key\":\"organization\",\"value\":\"Organization\"},{\"key\":\"validateUsersDn\",\"value\":\"You must enter users DN\"},{\"key\":\"cibaBackchannelTokenDeliveryMode\",\"value\":\"Backchannel Token Delivery Mode\"},{\"key\":\"validateAttributeName\",\"value\":\"Attribute configuration without name is not allowed.\"},{\"key\":\"smtpFromPlaceholder\",\"value\":\"Sender email address\"},{\"key\":\"deleteAllTranslationsError\",\"value\":\"Error removing translation(s), {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"permissionsScopeName\",\"value\":\"Scope-name\"},{\"key\":\"validPostLogoutRedirectURIsHelp\",\"value\":\"Valid URI pattern a browser can redirect to after a successful logout. A value of '+' or an empty field will use the list of valid redirect uris. A value of '-' will not allow any post logout redirect uris. Simple wildcards are allowed such as 'http://example.com/*'. Relative path can be specified too such as /my/relative/path/*. Relative paths are relative to the client root URL, or if none is specified the auth server root URL is used.\"},{\"key\":\"importKeysError\",\"value\":\"Error importing keys. {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"oauthDeviceAuthorizationGrant\",\"value\":\"OAuth 2.0 Device Authorization Grant\"},{\"key\":\"roleRemoveAssociatedRoleConfirm\",\"value\":\"Remove associated role?\"},{\"key\":\"httpPostBindingAuthnRequest\",\"value\":\"HTTP-POST binding for AuthnRequest\"},{\"key\":\"usersInRole\",\"value\":\"Users in role\"},{\"key\":\"updatedUserProfileError\",\"value\":\"User Profile configuration hasn't been saved: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"selectUser\",\"value\":\"Select a user whose identity is going to be used to query permissions from the server.\"},{\"key\":\"resultPermit\",\"value\":\"Result-Permit\"},{\"key\":\"ldapErrorCantEnableUnsyncedAndImportOff\",\"value\":\"Can not disable Importing users when LDAP provider mode is UNSYNCED\"},{\"key\":\"emptyAuthorizationScopes\",\"value\":\"No authorization scopes\"},{\"key\":\"bruteForceMode.Disabled\",\"value\":\"Disabled\"},{\"key\":\"removeAssociatedRoles\",\"value\":\"Remove associated roles\"},{\"key\":\"deleteFlowError\",\"value\":\"Could not delete flow: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"clientUpdaterSourceHost\",\"value\":\"The condition checks the host/domain of the entity who tries to create/update the client to determine whether the policy is applied.\"},{\"key\":\"signAssertions\",\"value\":\"Sign assertions\"},{\"key\":\"validateSignatures\",\"value\":\"Enable/disable signature validation of SAML responses.\"},{\"key\":\"addOrganizationId.help\",\"value\":\"If enabled, the organization id will be available for each organization mapped to the token.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.DELETE_ACCOUNT.name\",\"value\":\"Delete account\"},{\"key\":\"attestationPreference.indirect\",\"value\":\"Indirect\"},{\"key\":\"signatureAlgorithm\",\"value\":\"Signature algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmTranslationTitle\",\"value\":\"Delete translation(s)?\"},{\"key\":\"resetActions\",\"value\":\"Reset Actions\"},{\"key\":\"user\",\"value\":\"User\"},{\"key\":\"scopesAsRequested\",\"value\":\"Scopes are requested\"},{\"key\":\"updateErrorClientScope\",\"value\":\"Could not update client scope: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"useKerberosForPasswordAuthentication\",\"value\":\"Use Kerberos for password authentication\"},{\"key\":\"orgainzatinoDeleteError\",\"value\":\"Could not delete client: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"anonymousAccessPolicies\",\"value\":\"Anonymous access polices\"},{\"key\":\"createClient\",\"value\":\"Create client\"},{\"key\":\"validatePasswordPolicyHelp\",\"value\":\"Determines if Keycloak should validate the password with the realm password policy before updating it. For the case when user's password is saved in LDAP, some Keycloak password policies will not work (Not Recently Used, Expire Password, Hashing Iterations, Hashing Algorithm) due the fact that Keycloak does not have direct control over the password storage. It is needed to enable password policies at the LDAP server layer if you want to leverage those password policies.\"},{\"key\":\"createResourceSuccess\",\"value\":\"Resource created successfully\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmUsers_one\",\"value\":\"Delete user {{name}}?\"},{\"key\":\"addClientProfileError\",\"value\":\"Could not create client profile: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"search\",\"value\":\"Search\"},{\"key\":\"validateEditMode\",\"value\":\"You must select an edit mode\"},{\"key\":\"algorithmHelp\",\"value\":\"Intended algorithm for the key\"},{\"key\":\"ldapRolesDn\",\"value\":\"LDAP roles DN\"},{\"key\":\"welcomeText\",\"value\":\"Keycloak provides user federation, strong authentication, user management, fine-grained authorization, and more. Add authentication to applications and secure services with minimum effort. No need to deal with storing users or authenticating users.\"},{\"key\":\"updateReadOnlyAttributesRejectedMessage\",\"value\":\"Update of read-only attribute rejected\"},{\"key\":\"passwordConfirmation\",\"value\":\"Password confirmation\"},{\"key\":\"providerIdHelp\",\"value\":\"Provider ID\"},{\"key\":\"createAttribute\",\"value\":\"Create attribute\"},{\"key\":\"helpLabel\",\"value\":\"More help for '{{label}}'\"},{\"key\":\"Thursday\",\"value\":\"Thursday\"},{\"key\":\"isMandatoryInLdap\",\"value\":\"Is mandatory in LDAP\"},{\"key\":\"discoveryEndpoint\",\"value\":\"Discovery endpoint\"},{\"key\":\"claimValue\",\"value\":\"Claim Value\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.FEDERATED_IDENTITY_LINK.name\",\"value\":\"Federated identity link\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientConditionError\",\"value\":\"Error creating condition: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"editBtn\",\"value\":\"Edit button\"},{\"key\":\"used.notInUse\",\"value\":\"Not in use\"},{\"key\":\"emailSettings\",\"value\":\"Email settings\"},{\"key\":\"ldapErrorCantPreserveGroupInheritanceWithUIDMembershipType\",\"value\":\"Not possible to preserve group inheritance and use UID membership type together.\"},{\"key\":\"evictionHourHelp\",\"value\":\"Hour of the day the entry will become invalid\"},{\"key\":\"permissionDetails\",\"value\":\"Permission details\"},{\"key\":\"clientPoliciesProfiles\",\"value\":\"Client Policies Profiles\"},{\"key\":\"addToFilter\",\"value\":\"Add to filter\"},{\"key\":\"importResourceError\",\"value\":\"Could not import the resource due to {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"useMetadataDescriptorUrlHelp\",\"value\":\"If the switch is on, the certificates to validate signatures will be downloaded and cached from the given \\\"Metadata descriptor URL\\\". The \\\"Reload keys\\\" action can be used to refresh the certificates in the cache. If the switch is off, certificates from \\\"Validating X509 certificates\\\" option are used, they need to be manually updated when changed in the IDP.\"},{\"key\":\"noGroups\",\"value\":\"No groups\"},{\"key\":\"origin\",\"value\":\"Origin\"},{\"key\":\"rowCancelBtnAriaLabel\",\"value\":\"Cancel edits for {{messageBundle}}\"},{\"key\":\"showPasswordDataName\",\"value\":\"Name\"},{\"key\":\"whoCanEdit\",\"value\":\"Who can edit?\"},{\"key\":\"mappingCreatedSuccess\",\"value\":\"Mapping successfully created\"},{\"key\":\"selectCachePolicy\",\"value\":\"Select cache policy\"},{\"key\":\"keyAliasHelp\",\"value\":\"Alias for the private key\"},{\"key\":\"smtpPortPlaceholder\",\"value\":\"SMTP port (defaults to 25)\"},{\"key\":\"ellipticCurveHelp\",\"value\":\"Elliptic curve used in ECDSA\"},{\"key\":\"authenticatorRefConfig.maxAge.help\",\"value\":\"The max age in seconds that the authenticator reference value is good for in an SSO session. When the Authentication Method Reference (AMR) protocol mapper is used, the AMR will only be considered valid and populated in the token if the authenticator execution was completed within the specified max age.\"},{\"key\":\"attributesGroup\",\"value\":\"Attributes Group\"},{\"key\":\"ssoSessionMax\",\"value\":\"Max time before a session is expired. Tokens and browser sessions are invalidated when a session is expired.\"},{\"key\":\"joinGroupsFor\",\"value\":\"Join groups for user {{username}}\"},{\"key\":\"attributeConsumingServiceIndex\",\"value\":\"Attribute Consuming Service Index\"},{\"key\":\"assign\",\"value\":\"Assign\"},{\"key\":\"disableConfirmRealm\",\"value\":\"User and clients can't access the realm if it's disabled. Are you sure you want to continue?\"},{\"key\":\"includeInUserInfo.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Should the claim be added to the userinfo?\"},{\"key\":\"initialCounter\",\"value\":\"Initial counter\"},{\"key\":\"revokeRefreshTokenHelp\",\"value\":\"If enabled a refresh token can only be used up to 'Refresh Token Max Reuse' and is revoked when a different token is used. Otherwise refresh tokens are not revoked when used and can be used multiple times.\"},{\"key\":\"ownerManagedAccessHelp\",\"value\":\"If enabled, the access to this resource can be managed by the resource owner.\"},{\"key\":\"connectionAndAuthentication\",\"value\":\"Connection & Authentication\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopeType.optional\",\"value\":\"Optional\"},{\"key\":\"saveEventListenersError\",\"value\":\"Error saving event listener: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"inputOptionLabelsI18nPrefix\",\"value\":\"Internationalization key prefix\"},{\"key\":\"enabledHelp\",\"value\":\"Set if the keys are enabled\"},{\"key\":\"linkUpdatedSuccessful\",\"value\":\"Identity provider link successfully updated\"},{\"key\":\"admin-events-cleared-error\",\"value\":\"Could not clear the admin events {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"deleteExecutionSuccess\",\"value\":\"Execution successfully deleted\"},{\"key\":\"selectAuthorizationEncryptedResponseAlg\",\"value\":\"Select authorization encrypted response alg\"},{\"key\":\"testingConnection\",\"value\":\"Testing connection\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.OAUTH2_DEVICE_VERIFY_USER_CODE_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"OAuth2 device verify user code error\"},{\"key\":\"requiredClientScope\",\"value\":\"Please add at least one client scope.\"},{\"key\":\"searchForProvider\",\"value\":\"Search for provider\"},{\"key\":\"off\",\"value\":\"Off\"},{\"key\":\"updateSuccess\",\"value\":\"Provider successfully updated\"},{\"key\":\"skipCustomizationAndFinish\",\"value\":\"Skip customization and finish\"},{\"key\":\"flowDescriptionHelp\",\"value\":\"Help text for the description of the new flow\"},{\"key\":\"kc.time.date_time\",\"value\":\"Date/Time (MM/dd/yyyy hh:mm:ss)\"},{\"key\":\"clearKeysCacheHelp\",\"value\":\"Clears all entries from the cache of external public keys. These are keys of external clients or identity providers. This will clear all entries for all realms.\"},{\"key\":\"confirmAccessTokenBody\",\"value\":\"If you regenerate registration access token, the access data regarding the client registration service will be updated.\"},{\"key\":\"remainingCount\",\"value\":\"Remaining count\"},{\"key\":\"max-clients.tooltip\",\"value\":\"It will not be allowed to register a new client if count of existing clients in realm is same or bigger than the configured limit.\"},{\"key\":\"claim\",\"value\":\"Claim\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientScope_one\",\"value\":\"Delete client scope {{name}}\"},{\"key\":\"fetchRoles\",\"value\":\"Fetch Roles\"},{\"key\":\"providedBy\",\"value\":\"Provided by\"},{\"key\":\"doNotStoreUsers\",\"value\":\"Do not store users\"},{\"key\":\"themeType\",\"value\":\"Theme Type\"},{\"key\":\"noUsersFound\",\"value\":\"No users found\"},{\"key\":\"mappedGroupAttributesHelp\",\"value\":\"List of names of attributes divided by commas. This points to the list of attributes on LDAP group, which will be mapped as attributes of Group in Keycloak. Leave this empty if no additional group attributes are required to be mapped in Keycloak.\"},{\"key\":\"openIdConnectCompatibilityModes\",\"value\":\"OpenID Connect Compatibility Modes\"},{\"key\":\"code\",\"value\":\"Code\"},{\"key\":\"nameHelp\",\"value\":\"Help text for the name of the new flow\"},{\"key\":\"keys\",\"value\":\"Keys\"},{\"key\":\"defaultSigAlg\",\"value\":\"Default Signature Algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"resourcesToImport\",\"value\":\"Resources to import\"},{\"key\":\"selectRole.label\",\"value\":\"Select Role\"},{\"key\":\"isBinaryAttributeHelp\",\"value\":\"Should be true for binary LDAP attributes.\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnPolicyRpEntityName\",\"value\":\"Relying party entity name\"},{\"key\":\"enableStartTlsHelp\",\"value\":\"Encrypts the connection to LDAP using STARTTLS, which will disable connection pooling\"},{\"key\":\"resourceScopeSuccess\",\"value\":\"The authorization scope successfully deleted\"},{\"key\":\"userIdHelperText\",\"value\":\"Enter the unique ID of the user for this identity provider.\"},{\"key\":\"forwardParametersHelp\",\"value\":\"Non OpenID Connect/OAuth standard query parameters to be forwarded to external IDP from the initial application request to Authorization Endpoint. Multiple parameters can be entered, separated by comma (,).\"},{\"key\":\"changeAuthenticatorConfirmTitle\",\"value\":\"Change to {{clientAuthenticatorType}}?\"},{\"key\":\"admin-events-cleared\",\"value\":\"The admin events have been cleared\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_INITIATED_ACCOUNT_LINKING.description\",\"value\":\"Client initiated account linking\"},{\"key\":\"annotationsText\",\"value\":\"Annotations\"},{\"key\":\"loginThemeHelp\",\"value\":\"Select theme for login, OTP, grant, registration and forgot password pages.\"},{\"key\":\"oneTimePassword\",\"value\":\"One-Time Password\"},{\"key\":\"metadataDescriptorUrl\",\"value\":\"Metadata descriptor URL\"},{\"key\":\"excludeSessionStateFromAuthenticationResponseHelp\",\"value\":\"If this is on, the parameter 'session_state' will not be included in OpenID Connect Authentication Response. It is useful if the client uses an older OIDC / OAuth2 adapter, which does not support the 'session_state' parameter.\"},{\"key\":\"useRefreshTokenForClientCredentialsGrantHelp\",\"value\":\"If this is on, a refresh_token will be created and added to the token response if the client_credentials grant is used. The OAuth 2.0 RFC6749 Section 4.4.3 states that a refresh_token should not be generated when client_credentials grant is used. If this is off then no refresh_token will be generated and the associated user session will be removed.\"},{\"key\":\"userManagedAccess\",\"value\":\"User-managed access\"},{\"key\":\"vendorHelp\",\"value\":\"LDAP vendor (provider)\"},{\"key\":\"selectFilterType\",\"value\":\"Select filter type\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.PERMISSION_TOKEN_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Permission token error\"},{\"key\":\"validPostLogoutRedirectURIs\",\"value\":\"Valid URI pattern a browser can redirect to after a successful logout. A value of '+' or an empty field will use the list of valid redirect uris. A value of '-' will not allow any post logout redirect uris. Simple wildcards are allowed such as 'http://example.com/*'. Relative path can be specified too such as /my/relative/path/*. Relative paths are relative to the client root URL, or if none is specified the auth server root URL is used.\"},{\"key\":\"edit\",\"value\":\"Edit\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.INVALID_SIGNATURE_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Invalid signature error\"},{\"key\":\"addUri\",\"value\":\"Add URI\"},{\"key\":\"minus\",\"value\":\"Minus\"},{\"key\":\"includeGroupsAndRoles\",\"value\":\"Include groups and roles\"},{\"key\":\"enableHelpMode\",\"value\":\"Enable help mode\"},{\"key\":\"translationValue\",\"value\":\"Translation value\"},{\"key\":\"clientRegisterPolicyDeleteConfirm\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to permanently delete the client registration policy {{name}}\"},{\"key\":\"jsonEditor\",\"value\":\"JSON editor\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPoliciesHelp.forceExpiredPasswordChange\",\"value\":\"The number of days the password is valid before a new password is required.\"},{\"key\":\"envelopeFromHelp\",\"value\":\"An email address used for bounces (optional).\"},{\"key\":\"disableConfirmOrganization\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to disable this organization?\"},{\"key\":\"acrToLoAMappingHelp\",\"value\":\"Define which ACR (Authentication Context Class Reference) value is mapped to which LoA (Level of Authentication). The ACR can be any value, whereas the LoA must be numeric.\"},{\"key\":\"identityProviders\",\"value\":\"Identity providers\"},{\"key\":\"filteredByClaimHelp\",\"value\":\"If true, ID tokens issued by the identity provider must have a specific claim. Otherwise, the user can not authenticate through this broker.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.FEDERATED_IDENTITY_OVERRIDE_LINK_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Federated identity link override error\"},{\"key\":\"clientIdHelpHelp\",\"value\":\"Client ID of client to which LDAP role mappings will be mapped. Applicable only if 'Use Realm Roles Mapping' is false.\"},{\"key\":\"samlEntityDescriptor\",\"value\":\"SAML entity descriptor\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPolicyHintsEnabled\",\"value\":\"Password policy hints enabled\"},{\"key\":\"syncMode\",\"value\":\"Sync mode\"},{\"key\":\"details\",\"value\":\"Details\"},{\"key\":\"onDragStart\",\"value\":\"Dragging started for item {{item}}\"},{\"key\":\"clearButtonTitle\",\"value\":\"Clear\"},{\"key\":\"editInfo\",\"value\":\"Edit info\"},{\"key\":\"searchScope\",\"value\":\"Search scope\"},{\"key\":\"clientAccessType\",\"value\":\"It uses the client's access type (confidential, public, bearer-only) to determine whether the policy is applied. Condition is checked during most of OpenID Connect requests (Authorization requests, token requests, introspection endpoint request, etc.). Confidential client has enabled client authentication when public client has disabled client authentication. Bearer-only is a deprecated client type.\"},{\"key\":\"firstName\",\"value\":\"First name\"},{\"key\":\"noTranslationsInstructions\",\"value\":\"Add a translation to get started.\"},{\"key\":\"authorizationEncryptedResponseEncHelp\",\"value\":\"JWA Algorithm used for content encryption in encrypting the authorization response when the response mode is jwt. This option is needed if you want encrypted authorization response. If left empty, the authorization response is just signed, but not encrypted.\"},{\"key\":\"postBrokerLoginFlowAliasHelp\",\"value\":\"Alias of authentication flow, which is triggered after each login with this identity provider. Useful if you want additional verification of each user authenticated with this identity provider (for example OTP). Leave this to \\\"None\\\" if you need no any additional authenticators to be triggered after login with this identity provider. Also note that authenticator implementations must assume that user is already set in ClientSession as identity provider already set it.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UNREGISTER_NODE_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Unregister node error\"},{\"key\":\"sessionsType.allSessions\",\"value\":\"All session types\"},{\"key\":\"sessionsType.serviceAccount\",\"value\":\"Service account\"},{\"key\":\"clientSignatureHelp\",\"value\":\"Will the client sign their saml requests and responses? And should they be validated?\"},{\"key\":\"importOverwritten_other\",\"value\":\"{{count}} records overwritten.\"},{\"key\":\"kc.client.user_agent\",\"value\":\"Client/User Agent\"},{\"key\":\"addClientScopes\",\"value\":\"Add client scopes\"},{\"key\":\"doNotStoreUsersHelp\",\"value\":\"When enabled, users from this broker are not persisted in internal database.\"},{\"key\":\"userCreateError\",\"value\":\"Could not create user: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"AESKeySize\",\"value\":\"AES Key Size\"},{\"key\":\"aliasHelp\",\"value\":\"The alias uniquely identifies an identity provider and it is also used to build the redirect uri.\"},{\"key\":\"selectBindType\",\"value\":\"Select bind type\"},{\"key\":\"pairwiseClientRedirectURIsMultipleHosts\",\"value\":\"Without a configured Sector Identifier URI, client redirect URIs must not contain multiple host components.\"},{\"key\":\"bruteForceDetection\",\"value\":\"Brute force detection\"},{\"key\":\"loginTimeoutHelp\",\"value\":\"Max time a user has to complete a login. This is recommended to be relatively long, such as 30 minutes or more\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientProfile\",\"value\":\"Delete this client profile\"},{\"key\":\"none\",\"value\":\"None\"},{\"key\":\"createNewUser\",\"value\":\"Create new user\"},{\"key\":\"emptyClientProfiles\",\"value\":\"No profiles\"},{\"key\":\"rsaGenerated\",\"value\":\"rsa-generated\"},{\"key\":\"push\",\"value\":\"Push\"},{\"key\":\"periodicFullSyncHelp\",\"value\":\"Whether periodic full synchronization of LDAP users to Keycloak should be enabled or not\"},{\"key\":\"sendInvite\",\"value\":\"Send invite\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmFlow\",\"value\":\"Delete flow?\"},{\"key\":\"lastName\",\"value\":\"Last name\"},{\"key\":\"emptyAdminEvents\",\"value\":\"No admin events\"},{\"key\":\"excludeIssuerFromAuthenticationResponseHelp\",\"value\":\"If this is on, the parameter 'iss' will not be included in OpenID Connect Authentication Response. It is useful if the client uses an older OIDC / OAuth2 adapter, which does not support the 'iss' parameter.\"},{\"key\":\"artifactResolutionServiceHelp\",\"value\":\"SAML Artifact resolution service for the client. This is the endpoint to which Keycloak will send a SOAP ArtifactResolve message. You can leave this blank if you do not have a URL for this binding.\"},{\"key\":\"clientUpdaterTrustedHosts\",\"value\":\"Trusted Hosts\"},{\"key\":\"deleteSuccess\",\"value\":\"Attributes group deleted.\"},{\"key\":\"copy\",\"value\":\"Copy\"},{\"key\":\"emptyPermissionInstructions\",\"value\":\"If you want to create a permission, please click the button below to create a resource-based or scope-based permission.\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnPolicyAvoidSameAuthenticatorRegisterHelp\",\"value\":\"Avoid registering an authenticator that has already been registered.\"},{\"key\":\"supportedLocales\",\"value\":\"Supported locales\"},{\"key\":\"requiredClient\",\"value\":\"Please add at least one client.\"},{\"key\":\"passSubject\",\"value\":\"Pass subject\"},{\"key\":\"deleteFlowSuccess\",\"value\":\"Flow successfully deleted\"},{\"key\":\"referral\",\"value\":\"Referral\"},{\"key\":\"httpPostBindingLogoutHelp\",\"value\":\"Indicates whether to respond to requests using HTTP-POST binding. If false, HTTP-REDIRECT binding will be used.\"},{\"key\":\"clientAuthentication\",\"value\":\"Client authentication\"},{\"key\":\"createResource\",\"value\":\"Create resource\"},{\"key\":\"data\",\"value\":\"Data\"},{\"key\":\"clientAssertionSigningAlgHelp\",\"value\":\"Signature algorithm to create JWT assertion as client authentication. In the case of JWT signed with private key or JWT signed with client secret, it is required. If no algorithm is specified, the following algorithm is adapted. RS256 is adapted in the case of JWT signed with private key. HS256 is adapted in the case of JWT signed with client secret.\"},{\"key\":\"organizationSaveSuccess\",\"value\":\"Organization successfully saved.\"},{\"key\":\"noAvailableIdentityProviders\",\"value\":\"No available identity providers.\"},{\"key\":\"resource\",\"value\":\"Resource\"},{\"key\":\"profiles\",\"value\":\"Profiles\"},{\"key\":\"keysFilter.DISABLED\",\"value\":\"Disabled keys\"},{\"key\":\"link\",\"value\":\"Link\"},{\"key\":\"defaultGroupAddedError\",\"value\":\"Error adding group(s) to the default group {error}\"},{\"key\":\"selectMethodType.generate\",\"value\":\"Generate\"},{\"key\":\"chooseAPolicyProvider\",\"value\":\"Choose a policy provider\"},{\"key\":\"clientAuthenticationHelp\",\"value\":\"The client authentication method (cfr. https://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-core-1_0.html#ClientAuthentication). In case of JWT signed with private key, the realm private key is used.\"},{\"key\":\"hasWords\",\"value\":\"Has words\"},{\"key\":\"offlineSessionMax\",\"value\":\"Offline Session Max\"},{\"key\":\"generatedUserInfoHelp\",\"value\":\"See the example User Info, which will be provided by the User Info Endpoint\"},{\"key\":\"verifyEmailHelpText\",\"value\":\"Require user to verify their email address after initial login or after address changes are submitted.\"},{\"key\":\"groups\",\"value\":\"Groups\"},{\"key\":\"includeSubGroups\",\"value\":\"Include sub-group users\"},{\"key\":\"translationError\",\"value\":\"Please add translations before saving: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.PERMISSION_TOKEN.name\",\"value\":\"Permission token\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CUSTOM_REQUIRED_ACTION.description\",\"value\":\"Custom required action\"},{\"key\":\"searchByRoleName\",\"value\":\"Search by role name\"},{\"key\":\"addMultivaluedLabel\",\"value\":\"Add {{fieldLabel}}\"},{\"key\":\"displayName\",\"value\":\"Display name\"},{\"key\":\"inviteSentError\",\"value\":\"Could not sent invitation: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"addTranslationError\",\"value\":\"Error creating translation, {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"policyUrl\",\"value\":\"Policy URL\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPoliciesHelp.regexPattern\",\"value\":\"Requires that the password matches one or more defined Java regular expression patterns.\"},{\"key\":\"validRedirectURIsHelp\",\"value\":\"Valid URI pattern a browser can redirect to after a successful login. Simple wildcards are allowed such as 'http://example.com/*'. Relative path can be specified too such as /my/relative/path/*. Relative paths are relative to the client root URL, or if none is specified the auth server root URL is used. For SAML, you must set valid URI patterns if you are relying on the consumer service URL embedded with the login request.\"},{\"key\":\"usermodel.clientRoleMapping.clientId.label\",\"value\":\"Client ID\"},{\"key\":\"serviceProviderEntityId\",\"value\":\"Service provider entity ID\"},{\"key\":\"clientLoginTimeoutHelp\",\"value\":\"Max time a client has to finish the access token protocol. This should normally be 1 minute.\"},{\"key\":\"emptyUserEventsInstructions\",\"value\":\"There are no user events in this realm.\"},{\"key\":\"noRolesInstructions-clients\",\"value\":\"You haven't created any roles for this client scope. Create a role to get started.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_EMAIL.description\",\"value\":\"Update email\"},{\"key\":\"firstBrokerLoginFlowAliasOverride\",\"value\":\"First login flow override\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VALIDATE_ACCESS_TOKEN.description\",\"value\":\"Validate access token\"},{\"key\":\"sendIdTokenOnLogoutHelp\",\"value\":\"If the 'id_token_hint' parameter should be sent in logout requests.\"},{\"key\":\"addressClaim.postal_code.label\",\"value\":\"User Attribute Name for Postal Code\"},{\"key\":\"whoCanEditHelp\",\"value\":\"If enabled, users or administrators can view and edit the attribute. Otherwise, users or administrators don't have access to write to the attribute.\"},{\"key\":\"scopeNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of the client scope. Must be unique in the realm. Name should not contain space characters as it is used as value of scope parameter\"},{\"key\":\"noConsentsText\",\"value\":\"The consents will only be recorded when users try to access a client that is configured to require consent. In that case, users will get a consent page which asks them to grant access to the client.\"},{\"key\":\"userModelAttribute\",\"value\":\"User model attribute\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.LOGOUT_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Logout error\"},{\"key\":\"resetPasswordAllowed\",\"value\":\"Forgot password\"},{\"key\":\"expirationValueNotValid\",\"value\":\"Value should should be greater or equal to 1\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_CONSENT.name\",\"value\":\"Update consent\"},{\"key\":\"forceArtifactBinding\",\"value\":\"Force artifact binding\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.USER_DISABLED_BY_PERMANENT_LOCKOUT_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"User disabled by permanent lockout error\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REFRESH_TOKEN_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Refresh token error\"},{\"key\":\"selectAccessTokenSignatureAlgorithm\",\"value\":\"Select access token signature algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPolicy\",\"value\":\"Password policy\"},{\"key\":\"offlineSessionIdleHelp\",\"value\":\"Time an offline session is allowed to be idle before it expires. You need to use offline token to refresh at least once