 name on the client to make sure that particular client policy will be applied on requests of this client. Condition is checked during most of OpenID Connect requests (Authorization requests, token requests, introspection endpoint request, etc.)\"},{\"key\":\"validatingX509Certs\",\"value\":\"Validating X509 certificates\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_UPDATE.description\",\"value\":\"Client update\"},{\"key\":\"searchInitialAccessToken\",\"value\":\"Search token\"},{\"key\":\"defaultAdminInitiatedActionLifespanHelp\",\"value\":\"Maximum time before an action permit sent to a user by administrator is expired. This value is recommended to be long to allow administrators to send e-mails for users that are currently offline. The default timeout can be overridden immediately before issuing the token.\"},{\"key\":\"maxLifespanHelp\",\"value\":\"Max lifespan of cache entry in milliseconds\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_RESPONSE.name\",\"value\":\"Identity provider response\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.RESTART_AUTHENTICATION_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Restart authentication error\"},{\"key\":\"evictionHour\",\"value\":\"Eviction hour\"},{\"key\":\"ldapMappersList\",\"value\":\"LDAP Mappers\"},{\"key\":\"bindDnHelp\",\"value\":\"DN of the LDAP admin, which will be used by Keycloak to access LDAP server\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.TOKEN_EXCHANGE.description\",\"value\":\"Token exchange\"},{\"key\":\"continue\",\"value\":\"Continue\"},{\"key\":\"editProvider\",\"value\":\"Edit provider\"},{\"key\":\"backchannelLogoutUrlHelp\",\"value\":\"URL that will cause the client to log itself out when a logout request is sent to this realm (via end_session_endpoint). If omitted, no logout request will be sent to the client is this case.\"},{\"key\":\"updateScopeSuccess\",\"value\":\"Authorization scope successfully updated\"},{\"key\":\"authenticatorRefConfig.value.label\",\"value\":\"Authenticator Reference\"},{\"key\":\"inherent\",\"value\":\"Inherited\"},{\"key\":\"updateClientPolicySuccess\",\"value\":\"Client policy updated\"},{\"key\":\"attributeValue\",\"value\":\"Attribute Value\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_DELETE_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Client delete error\"},{\"key\":\"selectIdTokenSignatureAlgorithm\",\"value\":\"Select Id token signature algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"operationTypes\",\"value\":\"Operation types\"},{\"key\":\"loginWithEmailAllowed\",\"value\":\"Login with email\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CLIENT_LOGIN.name\",\"value\":\"Client login\"},{\"key\":\"mapper.nameid.format.tooltip\",\"value\":\"This mapper is applied only if the NameID format of the incoming AuthnRequest is equal to this value.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_PROFILE.description\",\"value\":\"Update profile\"},{\"key\":\"assignRolesTo\",\"value\":\"Assign roles to {{client}}\"},{\"key\":\"policyProvider.client-scope\",\"value\":\"Define conditions for your permissions where a set of one or more client scopes is permitted to access an object.\"},{\"key\":\"policyProvider.js\",\"value\":\"Define conditions for your permissions using JavaScript. It is one of the rule-based policy types supported by Keycloak, and provides flexibility to write any policy based on the Evaluation API.\"},{\"key\":\"krbPrincipalAttribute\",\"value\":\"Kerberos principal attribute\"},{\"key\":\"searchProfile\",\"value\":\"Search profile\"},{\"key\":\"showRemaining\",\"value\":\"Show ${remaining}\"},{\"key\":\"configure\",\"value\":\"Configure\"},{\"key\":\"noUsersEmptyStateDescription\",\"value\":\"Only the users with this role directly assigned will appear under this tab. If you need to find users assigned to this role, go to\"},{\"key\":\"requiredActionConfig\",\"value\":\"Configuration for {{name}}\"},{\"key\":\"otpPolicyCodeReusable\",\"value\":\"Reusable token\"},{\"key\":\"addRedirectUri\",\"value\":\"Add valid redirect URIs\"},{\"key\":\"used.DEFAULT\",\"value\":\"Default\"},{\"key\":\"authenticationCreateFlowHelp\",\"value\":\"Create flow\"},{\"key\":\"socialProfil