yName\",\"value\":\"Attribute [Friendly Name]\"},{\"key\":\"roleObjectClassesHelp\",\"value\":\"Object class (or classes) of the role object. It's divided by commas if more classes are needed. In typical LDAP deployment it could be 'groupOfNames'. In Active Directory it's usually 'group'.\"},{\"key\":\"theme\",\"value\":\"Theme\"},{\"key\":\"bruteForceStrategy\",\"value\":\"Strategy to increase wait time\"},{\"key\":\"groupRemove_one\",\"value\":\"Group removed\"},{\"key\":\"deleteNode\",\"value\":\"Delete node?\"},{\"key\":\"rdnLdapAttributeHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of the LDAP attribute, which is used as RDN (top attribute) of typical user DN. Usually it's the same as the Username LDAP attribute, however it is not required. For example for Active directory, it is common to use 'cn' as RDN attribute when username attribute might be 'sAMAccountName'.\"},{\"key\":\"addAaguids\",\"value\":\"Add AAGUID\"},{\"key\":\"clearAdminEvents\",\"value\":\"Clear admin events\"},{\"key\":\"noRolesAssociatedInstructions\",\"value\":\"To add roles to this role press the 'Add role' button\"},{\"key\":\"alwaysDisplayInUIHelp\",\"value\":\"Always list this client in the Account UI, even if the user does not have an active session.\"},{\"key\":\"realmSaveSuccess\",\"value\":\"Realm successfully updated\"},{\"key\":\"executorTypeTextHelpText\",\"value\":\"Executor Type Text Help Text\"},{\"key\":\"readTimeout\",\"value\":\"Read timeout\"},{\"key\":\"createUser\",\"value\":\"Create user\"},{\"key\":\"policyDeletedSuccess\",\"value\":\"The Policy successfully deleted\"},{\"key\":\"iconUri\",\"value\":\"Icon URI\"},{\"key\":\"allowed-protocol-mappers.label\",\"value\":\"Allowed Protocol Mappers\"},{\"key\":\"group\",\"value\":\"Group\"},{\"key\":\"addAssociatedRolesText\",\"value\":\"Add associated roles\"},{\"key\":\"groupsClaimHelp\",\"value\":\"If defined, the policy will fetch user's groups from the given claim within an access token or ID token representing the identity asking permissions. If not defined, user's groups are obtained from your realm configuration.\"},{\"key\":\"certSubject\",\"value\":\"CERT_SUBJECT\"},{\"key\":\"requestObjectSignatureAlgorithm\",\"value\":\"Request object signature algorithm\"},{\"key\":\"tokenLifespan.expires\",\"value\":\"Expires in\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopeSuccess\",\"value\":\"Scope mapping updated\"},{\"key\":\"credentials\",\"value\":\"Credentials\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnPolicyCreateTimeoutHelp\",\"value\":\"The timeout value for creating the user's public key credential in seconds. If set to 0, this timeout option is not adapted.\"},{\"key\":\"general\",\"value\":\"General\"},{\"key\":\"failureFactor\",\"value\":\"Max login failures\"},{\"key\":\"updateClientPoliciesSuccess\",\"value\":\"The client policies configuration was updated\"},{\"key\":\"save-admin-eventsHelp\",\"value\":\"If enabled, admin events are saved to the database, which makes events available to the Admin UI.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.FEDERATED_IDENTITY_LINK.description\",\"value\":\"Federated identity link\"},{\"key\":\"userEvents\",\"value\":\"User events\"},{\"key\":\"otpPolicyPeriodErrorHint\",\"value\":\"Value needs to be between 1 second and 2 minutes\"},{\"key\":\"rowSaveBtnAriaLabel\",\"value\":\"Save edits for {{messageBundle}}\"},{\"key\":\"clear\",\"value\":\"Clear\"},{\"key\":\"deletedErrorClientScope\",\"value\":\"Could not delete client scope: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"client-updater-source-groups.label\",\"value\":\"Groups\"},{\"key\":\"selectLocales\",\"value\":\"Select locales\"},{\"key\":\"error-person-name-invalid-character\",\"value\":\"'{{0}}' contains invalid character.\"},{\"key\":\"endpointsHelp\",\"value\":\"Shows the configuration of the Service Provider endpoint\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.OAUTH2_EXTENSION_GRANT_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"OAuth2 extension grant error\"},{\"key\":\"locale_ar\",\"value\":\"Arabic (ž¦┘äž╣ž▒ž©┘Ŗž®)\"},{\"key\":\"mapperTypeLdapAttributeMapper\",\"value\":\"hardcoded-ldap-attribute-mapper\"},{\"key\":\"createClientPolicyError\",\"value\":\"Could not  create policy due to: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"mapperNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of the mapper\"},{\"key\":\"deleteMappingTitle\",\"value\":\"Delete mapping?\"},{\"key\":\"useTruststoreSpiHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies whether LDAP connection will use the Truststore SPI with the truststore configured in command-line options. 'Always' means that it will always use it. 'Never' means that it will not use it. Note that even if Keycloak truststore is not configured, the default java cacerts or certificate specified by 'javax.net.ssl.trustStore' property will be used.\"},{\"key\":\"realmCertificateAlias\",\"value\":\"Realm certificate alias\"},{\"key\":\"roleName\",\"value\":\"Role name\"},{\"key\":\"actionTokens\",\"value\":\"Action tokens\"},{\"key\":\"includeOneTimeUseConditionHelp\",\"value\":\"Should a OneTimeUse Condition be included in login responses?\"},{\"key\":\"availableIdPsText\",\"value\":\"All the configured identity providers in this realm are listed here. You can link the user account to any of the IdP accounts.\"},{\"key\":\"accessTokenLifespanHelp\",\"value\":\"Max time before an access token is expired. This value is recommended to be short relative to the SSO timeout\"},{\"key\":\"permissionsEnabled\",\"value\":\"Permissions enabled\"},{\"key\":\"attestationPreference.none\",\"value\":\"None\"},{\"key\":\"pairwiseSubAlgorithmSalt.label\",\"value\":\"Salt\"},{\"key\":\"locale_ca\",\"value\":\"Catalan (Catal├Ā)\"},{\"key\":\"locale_pt-BR\",\"value\":\"Portuguese (Brazil) (Portugu├¬s (Brasil))\"},{\"key\":\"useEntityDescriptor\",\"value\":\"Use entity descriptor\"},{\"key\":\"searchForTranslation\",\"value\":\"Search for translation\"},{\"key\":\"loginActionTimeout\",\"value\":\"Login action timeout\"},{\"key\":\"windowsDomainQN\",\"value\":\"Windows Domain Qualified Name\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientError\",\"value\":\"Could not delete profile: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"validRedirectURIs\",\"value\":\"Valid URI pattern a browser can redirect to after a successful login. Simple wildcards are allowed such as 'http://example.com/*'. Relative path can be specified too such as /my/relative/path/*. Relative paths are relative to the client root URL, or if none is specified the auth server root URL is used. For SAML, you must set valid URI patterns if you are relying on the consumer service URL embedded with the login request.\"},{\"key\":\"UPDATE_PROFILE\",\"value\":\"Update Profile (UPDATE_PROFILE)\"},{\"key\":\"assertionConsumerServicePostBindingURL\",\"value\":\"Assertion Consumer Service POST Binding URL\"},{\"key\":\"roleSaveError\",\"value\":\"Could not save role: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"membershipUserLdapAttributeHelp\",\"value\":\"Used just if Membership Attribute Type is UID. It is the name of the LDAP attribute on user, which is used for membership mappings. Usually it will be 'uid'. For example if the value of 'Membership User LDAP Attribute' is 'uid' and  LDAP group has 'memberUid: john', then it is expected that particular LDAP user will have attribute 'uid: john'.\"},{\"key\":\"linkSuccessful\",\"value\":\"Identity provider successfully linked to organization\"},{\"key\":\"accessTokenSignatureAlgorithmHelp\",\"value\":\"JWA algorithm used for signing access tokens.\"},{\"key\":\"signatureAlgorithmHelp\",\"value\":\"The signature algorithm to use to sign documents. Note that 'SHA1' based algorithms are deprecated and can be removed in the future. It is recommended to stick to some more secure algorithm instead of '*_SHA1'\"},{\"key\":\"addExecutionHelp\",\"value\":\"Execution can have a wide range of actions, from sending a reset email to validating an OTP\"},{\"key\":\"noLanguagesInstructions\",\"value\":\"Add a language in Realm settings > Localization > Locales to get started.\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPoliciesHelp.notUsername\",\"value\":\"The password cannot match the username.\"},{\"key\":\"locale_es\",\"value\":\"Spanish (Espa├▒ol)\"},{\"key\":\"authnContextDeclRefs\",\"value\":\"AuthnContext DeclRefs\"},{\"key\":\"standardFlow\",\"value\":\"Standard flow\"},{\"key\":\"votedToStatus\",\"value\":\" voted to {{status}}\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopeType.default\",\"value\":\"Default\"},{\"key\":\"locale_el\",\"value\":\"Greek (╬Ģ╬╗╬╗╬Ę╬Į╬╣╬║╬¼)\"},{\"key\":\"locale_en\",\"value\":\"English\"},{\"key\":\"locale_de\",\"value\":\"German (Deutsch)\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmTitle_one\",\"value\":\"Delete group?\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnUpdateSuccess\",\"value\":\"Updated webauthn policies successfully\"},{\"key\":\"onDragMove\",\"value\":\"Dragging item {{item}}\"},{\"key\":\"deleteScopeConfirm\",\"value\":\"If you delete this authorization scope, some permissions will be affected.\"},{\"key\":\"updateOtpSuccess\",\"value\":\"OTP policy successfully updated\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_LINK_ACCOUNT.name\",\"value\":\"Identity provider link account\"},{\"key\":\"enableClientSignatureRequiredModal\",\"value\":\"Enable client signature required\"},{\"key\":\"owner\",\"value\":\"Owner\"},{\"key\":\"locale_fr\",\"value\":\"French (Fran├¦ais)\"},{\"key\":\"mapperTypeMsadUserAccountControlManagerHelp\",\"value\":\"Mapper specific to MSAD. It's able to integrate the MSAD user account state into Keycloak account state (account enabled, password is expired etc). It's using userAccountControl and pwdLastSet MSAD attributes for that. For example if pwdLastSet is 0, the Keycloak user is required to update the password; if userAccountControl is 514 (disabled account) the Keycloak user is disabled as well etc. Mapper is also able to handle the exception code from LDAP user authentication.\"},{\"key\":\"home\",\"value\":\"Home\"},{\"key\":\"locale_fa\",\"value\":\"Persian (┘üž¦ž▒ž│█ī)\"},{\"key\":\"effectiveMessageBundlesDescription\",\"value\":\"An effective message bundle is the set of translations for a given language, theme, and theme type. It also takes into account any realm overrides, which will take precedence.\"},{\"