 groups to Keycloak\"},{\"key\":\"noCredentialsText\",\"value\":\"This user does not have any credentials. You can set password for this user.\"},{\"key\":\"validatingPublicKey\",\"value\":\"Validating public key\"},{\"key\":\"permissionsListIntro\",\"value\":\"Edit the permission list by clicking the scope-name. It then redirects to the permission details page of the client named <1>{{realm}}</1>\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientConditionSuccess\",\"value\":\"Condition deleted successfully.\"},{\"key\":\"invalidPasswordMinSpecialCharsMessage\",\"value\":\"Invalid password: must contain at least {0} special characters.\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmIdentityProvider\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to permanently delete the provider '{{provider}}'?\"},{\"key\":\"organizations\",\"value\":\"Organizations\"},{\"key\":\"batchSize\",\"value\":\"Batch size\"},{\"key\":\"client-scopes-condition.tooltip\",\"value\":\"The list of expected client scopes. Condition evaluates to true if specified client request matches some of the client scopes. It depends also whether it should be default or optional client scope based on the 'Scope Type' configured.\"},{\"key\":\"locale_zh-TW\",\"value\":\"Chinese (Traditional) (õĖŁµ¢ć (ń╣üķ½ö))\"},{\"key\":\"xXSSProtection\",\"value\":\"X-XSS-Protection\"},{\"key\":\"usedMemory\",\"value\":\"Used memory\"},{\"key\":\"documentation\",\"value\":\"Documentation\"},{\"key\":\"fullNameLdapReadOnlyHelp\",\"value\":\"For Read-only, data is imported from LDAP to Keycloak DB, but it's not saved back to LDAP when the user is updated in Keycloak.\"},{\"key\":\"clientRootURLFragmentError\",\"value\":\"Root URL must not contain an URL fragment\"},{\"key\":\"overallResults\",\"value\":\"Overall Results\"},{\"key\":\"termsOfServiceUrlHelp\",\"value\":\"URL that the Relying Party Client provides to the End-User to read about the Relying Party's terms of service\"},{\"key\":\"client-roles.label\",\"value\":\"Client Roles\"},{\"key\":\"error-empty\",\"value\":\"Please specify value of '{{0}}'.\"},{\"key\":\"welcomeTabTitle\",\"value\":\"Welcome\"},{\"key\":\"cacheSettings\",\"value\":\"Cache settings\"},{\"key\":\"searchForClient\",\"value\":\"Search for client\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.UPDATE_PROFILE.name\",\"value\":\"Update profile\"},{\"key\":\"realmId\",\"value\":\"Realm ID\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.PERMISSION_TOKEN_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Permission token error\"},{\"key\":\"userVerify.discouraged\",\"value\":\"Discouraged\"},{\"key\":\"importFile\",\"value\":\"Import file\"},{\"key\":\"userInvitedOrganization_one\",\"value\":\"Invite to user sent\"},{\"key\":\"displayOnClientHelp\",\"value\":\"Applicable only if 'Consent Required' is on for this client. If this switch is off, the consent screen will contain just the consents corresponding to configured client scopes. If on, there will be also one item on the consent screen about this client itself.\"},{\"key\":\"noRoles\",\"value\":\"No roles for this user\"},{\"key\":\"importOverwritten_one\",\"value\":\"One record overwritten.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REGISTER_NODE_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Register node error\"},{\"key\":\"managePriorities\",\"value\":\"Manage priorities\"},{\"key\":\"createClientPolicySuccess\",\"value\":\"New policy created\"},{\"key\":\"frontendUrlHelp\",\"value\":\"Set the frontend URL for the realm. Use in combination with the default hostname provider to override the base URL for frontend requests for a specific realm.\"},{\"key\":\"generatedIdTokenHelp\",\"value\":\"See the example ID Token, which will be generated and sent to the client when selected user is authenticated. You can see claims and roles that the token will contain based on the effective protocol mappers and role scope mappings and also based on the claims/roles assigned to user himself\"},{\"key\":\"passwordPoliciesHelp.specialChars\",\"value\":\"The number of special characters required in the password string.\"},{\"key\":\"eventListeners\",\"value\":\"Event listeners\"},{\"key\":\"disableConfirmUserTitle\",\"value\":\"Disable user?\"},{\"key\":\"bindDn\",\"value\":\"Bind DN\"},{\"key\":\"saveProviderListSuccess\",\"value\":\"The priority of the provider has been updated successfully.\"},{\"key\":\"copyToClipboard\",\"value\":\"Copy to clipboard\"},{\"key\":\"wantAuthnRequestsSigned\",\"value\":\"Want AuthnRequests signed\"},{\"key\":\"usermodel.attr.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Name of stored user attribute which is the name of an attribute within the UserModel.attribute map.\"},{\"key\":\"mapperTypeHardcodedLdapRoleMapper\",\"value\":\"hardcoded-ldap-role-mapper\"},{\"key\":\"noResultsFound\",\"value\":\"No results found\"},{\"key\":\"addressClaim.region.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Name of User Attribute, which will be used to map to 'region' subclaim inside 'address' token claim. Defaults to 'region' .\"},{\"key\":\"IDK-periodicChangedUsersSyncHelp\",\"value\":\"Should newly created users be created within LDAP store? Priority affects which provider is chosen to sync the new user.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.REMOVE_FEDERATED_IDENTITY_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Remove federated identity error\"},{\"key\":\"verifyEmail\",\"value\":\"Verify email\"},{\"key\":\"addressClaim.locality.label\",\"value\":\"User Attribute Name for Locality\"},{\"key\":\"formatOption\",\"value\":\"Format option\"},{\"key\":\"clientScopeTypes.none\",\"value\":\"None\"},{\"key\":\"addSubFlowHelp\",\"value\":\"Sub-Flows can be either generic or form. The form type is used to construct a sub-flow that generates a single flow for the user. Sub-flows are a special type of execution that evaluate as successful depending on how the executions they contain evaluate.\"},{\"key\":\"tokenClaimName.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Name of the claim to insert into the token. This can be a fully qualified name like 'address.street'. In this case, a nested json object will be created. To prevent nesting and use dot literally, escape the dot with backslash (\\\\.).\"},{\"key\":\"clientProfileDescription\",\"value\":\"Description\"},{\"key\":\"fromPredefinedMapper\",\"value\":\"From predefined mappers\"},{\"key\":\"setup\",\"value\":\"Setup\"},{\"key\":\"unlinkAccount\",\"value\":\"Unlink account\"},{\"key\":\"showAuthData\",\"value\":\"Show authorization data\"},{\"key\":\"selectUnmanagedAttributePolicy\",\"value\":\"Select unmanaged attribute policy\"},{\"key\":\"select\",\"value\":\"Select\"},{\"key\":\"advanced\",\"value\":\"Advanced\"},{\"key\":\"addCondition\",\"value\":\"Add condition\"},{\"key\":\"updateSuccessClientScope\",\"value\":\"Client scope updated\"},{\"key\":\"permissionsDisableConfirm\",\"value\":\"If you disable the permissions, all the permissions in the list below will be delete automatically. In addition, the resources and scopes that are related will be removed\"},{\"key\":\"inviteMember\",\"value\":\"Invite member\"},{\"key\":\"clientProfilesHelpItem\",\"value\":\"Client profiles help item\"},{\"key\":\"messageBundleDescription\",\"value\":\"You can only edit the supported locales. If you haven't selected supported locales yet, you can only edit the English locale.\"},{\"key\":\"keyProviderMapperNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Display name of provider when linked in admin console.\"},{\"key\":\"isBinaryAttribute\",\"value\":\"Is binary attribute\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_RETRIEVE_TOKEN_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Identity provider retrieve token error\"},{\"key\":\"displayNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Friendly name for Identity Providers.\"},{\"key\":\"template\",\"value\":\"Template\"},{\"key\":\"clearCacheSuccess\",\"value\":\"Cache cleared successfully\"},{\"key\":\"identityProviderUnlinkConfirm\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to unlink this identity provider?\"},{\"key\":\"executorDetails\",\"value\":\"Executor details\"},{\"key\":\"usermodel.realmRoleMapping.rolePrefix.tooltip\",\"value\":\"A prefix which will be prepended to each Realm Role name (optional).\"},{\"key\":\"emptyEffectiveMessageBundles\",\"value\":\"Search for effective messages\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.INTROSPECT_TOKEN.description\",\"value\":\"Introspect token\"},{\"key\":\"displayOrderHelp\",\"value\":\"Number defining the order of the providers in GUI (for example, on the Login page). The lowest number will be applied first.\"},{\"key\":\"ldapSearchingAndUpdatingSettingsDescription\",\"value\":\"This section contains options related to searching the LDAP server for the available users.\"},{\"key\":\"allowed-client-scopes.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Whitelist of the client scopes, which can be used on a newly registered client. Attempt to register client with some client scope, which is not whitelisted, will be rejected. By default, the whitelist is either empty or contains just realm default client scopes (based on 'Allow Default Scopes' configuration property)\"},{\"key\":\"frontchannelLogoutHelp\",\"value\":\"When true, logout requires a browser redirect to client. When false, server performs a background invocation for logout.\"},{\"key\":\"isMandatoryInLdapHelp\",\"value\":\"If true, attribute is mandatory in LDAP. Hence if there is no value in Keycloak DB, the empty value will be set to be propagated to LDAP.\"},{\"key\":\"client-accesstype.label\",\"value\":\"Client Access Type\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_POST_LOGIN_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Identity provider post login error\"},{\"key\":\"mappingDeletedSuccess\",\"value\":\"Mapping successfully deleted\"},{\"key\":\"welcomeTo\",\"value\":\"Welcome to {{realmDisplayInfo}}\"},{\"key\":\"loggedInAsTempAdminUser\",\"value\":\"You are logged in as a temporary admin user. To harden security, create a permanent admin account and delete the temporary one.\"},{\"key\":\"principalType\",\"value\":\"Principal type\"},{\"key\":\"ignoreMissingGroupsHelp\",\"value\":\"Ignore missing groups in the group hierarchy.\"},{\"key\":\"createAttributeSuccess\",\"value\":\"Success! User Profile configuration has been saved.\"},{\"key\":\"annotations\",\"value\":\"Annotations\"},{\"key\":\"requiredWhen\",\"value\":\"Required when\"},{\"key\":\"top-level-flow-type.client-flow\",\"value\":\"Client flow\"},{\"key\":\"ipAddress\",\"value\":\"IP address\"},{\"key\":\"spi\",\"value\":\"SPI\"},{\"key\":\"serverInfo\",\"value\":\"Server info\"},{\"key\":\"emailThemeHelp\",\"value\":\"Select a theme for emails that are sent by the server.\"},{\"key\":\"Wednesday\",\"value\":\"Wednesday\"},{\"key\":\"nameHelpHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of the mapper\"},{\"key\":\"unmanagedAttributesHelpText\",\"value\":\"Unmanaged attributes are user attributes not explicitly defined in the user profile configuration. By default, unmanaged attributes are `Disabled` and are not available from any context such as registration, account, and the administration console. By setting `Enabled`, unmanaged attributes are fully recognized by the server and accessible through all contexts, useful if you are starting migrating an existing realm to the declarative user profile and you don't have yet all user attributes defined in the user profile configuration. By setting `Only administrators can write`, unmanaged attributes can be managed only through the administration console and API, useful if you have already defined any custom attribute that can be managed by users but you are unsure about adding other attributes that should only be managed by administrators. By setting `Only administrators can view`, unmanaged attributes are read-only and only available through the administration console and API.\"},{\"key\":\"flowNameHelp\",\"value\":\"Help text for the name of the new flow\"},{\"key\":\"deleteDialogTitle\",\"value\":\"Delete attribute group?\"},{\"key\":\"ldapAttributeName\",\"value\":\"LDAP attribute name\"},{\"key\":\"acceptsPromptNone\",\"value\":\"Accepts prompt=none forward from client\"},{\"key\":\"client-accesstype.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Access Type of the client, for which the condition will be applied. Confidential client has enabled client authentication when public client has disabled client authentication. Bearer-only is a deprecated client type.\"},{\"key\":\"evictionDay\",\"value\":\"Eviction day\"},{\"key\":\"upAttributeNameHelp\",\"value\":\"The name of the user attribute, used to uniquely identify an attribute.\"},{\"key\":\"couldNotFetchClientRoleMappings\",\"value\":\"Could not fetch client role mappings: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"filterGroups\",\"value\":\"Filter groups\"},{\"key\":\"locale_zh-CN\",\"value\":\"Chinese (Simplified) (õĖŁµ¢ć (ń«ĆõĮō))\"},{\"key\":\"userProfileSuccess\",\"value\":\"User profile settings successfully updated.\"},{\"key\":\"attributeDefaultValueHelp\",\"value\":\"If there is no value in Keycloak DB and attribute is mandatory in LDAP, this value will be propagated to LDAP.\"},{\"key\":\"Saturday\",\"value\":\"Saturday\"},{\"key\":\"membershipAttributeTypeHelp\",\"value\":\"DN means that LDAP group has it's members declared in form of their full DN. For example 'member: uid=john,ou=users,dc=example,dc=com'. UID means that LDAP group has it's members declared in form of pure user uids. For example 'memberUid: john'.\"},{\"key\":\"emptyResourcesInstructions\",\"value\":\"If you want to create a resource, please click the button below.\"},{\"key\":\"otpSupportedApplications.totpAppFreeOTPName\",\"value\":\"FreeOTP\"},{\"key\":\"recommendedSsoTimeout\",\"value\":\"It is recommended for this value to be shorter than the SSO session idle timeout: {{time}}\"},{\"key\":\"sessionExplain\",\"value\":\"Sessions are sessions of users in this realm and the clients that they access within the session.\"},{\"key\":\"executeActions\",\"value\":\"Execute actions\"},{\"key\":\"deny\",\"value\":\"Deny\"},{\"key\":\"moveGroupSuccess\",\"value\":\"Group moved\"},{\"key\":\"userDeletedError\",\"value\":\"The user could not be deleted {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"ldapGroupsDnHelp\",\"value\":\"LDAP DN where groups of this tree are saved. For example 'ou=groups,dc=example,dc=org'\"},{\"key\":\"readOnly\",\"value\":\"Read only\"},{\"key\":\"resultDeny\",\"value\":\"Result-Deny\"},{\"key\":\"kc.client.network.host\",\"value\":\"Client Host\"},{\"key\":\"removeMember\",\"value\":\"Remove member\"},{\"key\":\"clientIdHelp\",\"value\":\"The client identifier registered with the identity provider.\"},{\"key\":\"oAuthDeviceCodeLifespan\",\"value\":\"OAuth 2.0 Device Code Lifespan\"},{\"key\":\"clientSaveSuccess\",\"value\":\"Client successfully updated\"},{\"key\":\"oAuthDevicePollingInterval\",\"value\":\"OAuth 2.0 Device Polling Interval\"},{\"key\":\"conditions\",\"value\":\"Conditions\"},{\"key\":\"offlineSessionMaxHelp\",\"value\":\"Max time before an offline session is expired regardless of activity.\"},{\"key\":\"clientsClientScopesHelp\",\"value\":\"The scopes associated with this resource.\"},{\"key\":\"updateCredentialUserLabelError\",\"value\":\"Error changing user label: {{error}}\"},{\"key\":\"mappingCreatedError\",\"value\":\"Could not create mapping: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"uploadFile\",\"value\":\"Upload JSON file\"},{\"key\":\"importUsers\",\"value\":\"Import users\"},{\"key\":\"authenticationFlow\",\"value\":\"Authentication flow\"},{\"key\":\"deleteClientPolicySuccess\",\"value\":\"Client policy deleted\"},{\"key\":\"mapperTypeCertificateLdapMapper\",\"value\":\"certificate-ldap-mapper\"},{\"key\":\"clientAuthentications.client_secret_basic\",\"value\":\"Client secret sent as basic auth\"},{\"key\":\"permissionDecisionStrategyHelp\",\"value\":\"The decision strategy dictates how the policies associated with a given permission are evaluated and how a final decision is obtained. 'Affirmative' means that at least one policy must evaluate to a positive decision in order for the final decision to be also positive. 'Unanimous' means that all policies must evaluate to a positive decision in order for the final decision to be also positive. 'Consensus' means that the number of positive decisions must be greater than the number of negative decisions. If the number of positive and negative is the same, the final decision will be negative.\"},{\"key\":\"initialAccessTokenDetails\",\"value\":\"Initial access token details\"},{\"key\":\"removeConfirmOrganizationTitle\",\"value\":\"Remove organization?\"},{\"key\":\"inputTypeSize\",\"value\":\"Input size\"},{\"key\":\"subjectHelp\",\"value\":\"A regular expression for validating Subject DN in the Client Certificate. Use \\\"(.*?)(?:$)\\\" to match all kind of expressions.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.CUSTOM_REQUIRED_ACTION.name\",\"value\":\"Custom required action\"},{\"key\":\"moveGroupEmpty\",\"value\":\"No sub groups\"},{\"key\":\"rolesHelp\",\"value\":\"Select the roles you want to associate with the selected user.\"},{\"key\":\"enableLdapv3PasswordHelp\",\"value\":\"Use the LDAPv3 Password Modify Extended Operation (RFC-3062). The password modify extended operation usually requires that LDAP user already has password in the LDAP server. So when this is used with 'Sync Registrations', it can be good to add also 'Hardcoded LDAP attribute mapper' with randomly generated initial password.\"},{\"key\":\"pushedAuthorizationRequestRequired\",\"value\":\"Pushed authorization request required\"},{\"key\":\"generate\",\"value\":\"Generate\"},{\"key\":\"disableSigning\",\"value\":\"Disable \\\"{{key}}\\\"\"},{\"key\":\"periodicChangedUsersSync\",\"value\":\"Periodic changed users sync\"},{\"key\":\"importAdded_one\",\"value\":\"One record added.\"},{\"key\":\"emptySecondaryAction\",\"value\":\"Configure a new mapper\"},{\"key\":\"noRolesInstructions\",\"value\":\"You haven't assigned any roles to this user. Assign a role to get started.\"},{\"key\":\"allowKerberosAuthenticationHelp\",\"value\":\"Enable/disable HTTP authentication of users with SPNEGO/Kerberos tokens. The data about authenticated users will be provisioned from this LDAP server.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.OAUTH2_EXTENSION_GRANT.name\",\"value\":\"OAuth2 extension grant\"},{\"key\":\"user-events-cleared\",\"value\":\"The user events have been cleared\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirm\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to permanently delete the provider '{{provider}}'?\"},{\"key\":\"fullName\",\"value\":\"{{givenName}} {{familyName}}\"},{\"key\":\"selectRealm\",\"value\":\"Select realm\"},{\"key\":\"noIdentityProvider\",\"value\":\"No identity providers in this realm\"},{\"key\":\"updatedUserProfileSuccess\",\"value\":\"User Profile configuration has been saved\"},{\"key\":\"deleteProviderMapper\",\"value\":\"Delete mapper?\"},{\"key\":\"clientsPermissionsHint\",\"value\":\"Fine grained permissions for administrators that want to manage this client or apply roles defined by this client.\"},{\"key\":\"searchGroups\",\"value\":\"Search groups\"},{\"key\":\"trusted-hosts.tooltip\",\"value\":\"List of Hosts, which are trusted and are allowed to invoke Client Registration Service and/or be used as values of Client URIs. You can use hostnames or IP addresses. If you use star at the beginning (for example '*.example.com' ) then whole domain example.com will be trusted.\"},{\"key\":\"disableNonceHelp\",\"value\":\"Do not send the nonce parameter in the authentication request. The nonce parameter is sent and verified by default.\"},{\"key\":\"seconds\",\"value\":\"Seconds\"},{\"key\":\"viewDocumentation\",\"value\":\"Refer to documentation\"},{\"key\":\"keysFilter.ACTIVE\",\"value\":\"Active keys\"},{\"key\":\"krbPrincipalAttributeHelp\",\"value\":\"Name of the LDAP attribute, which refers to Kerberos principal. This is used to lookup appropriate LDAP user after successful Kerberos/SPNEGO authentication in Keycloak. When this is empty, the LDAP user will be looked based on LDAP username corresponding to the first part of his Kerberos principal. For instance, for principal 'john@KEYCLOAK.ORG', it will assume that LDAP username is 'john'.\"},{\"key\":\"addTranslationsDialogRowsTable\",\"value\":\"Add a translations dialog rows table\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.IDENTITY_PROVIDER_RESPONSE_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Identity provider response error\"},{\"key\":\"targetClaimHelp\",\"value\":\"Specifies the target claim which the policy will fetch.\"},{\"key\":\"scopePermissions.users.user-impersonated-description\",\"value\":\"Policies that decide which users can be impersonated.  These policies are applied to the user being impersonated.\"},{\"key\":\"isAccessTokenJWT\",\"value\":\"Access Token is JWT\"},{\"key\":\"deleteConfirmDialog_one\",\"value\":\"Are you sure you want to permanently delete {{count}} selected user\"},{\"key\":\"selectLoginTheme\",\"value\":\"Select login theme\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.AUTHREQID_TO_TOKEN_ERROR.name\",\"value\":\"Authreqid to token error\"},{\"key\":\"memberofLdapAttribute\",\"value\":\"Member-of LDAP attribute\"},{\"key\":\"webAuthnPolicyAttestationConveyancePreference\",\"value\":\"Attestation conveyance preference\"},{\"key\":\"clientRedirectURIsInvalid\",\"value\":\"A redirect URI is not a valid URI\"},{\"key\":\"rename\",\"value\":\"Rename\"},{\"key\":\"includeInLightweight.tooltip\",\"value\":\"Should the claim be added to the lightweight access token?\"},{\"key\":\"deleteNodeFail\",\"value\":\"Could not delete node: '{{error}}'\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.TOKEN_EXCHANGE_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Token exchange error\"},{\"key\":\"firstBrokerLoginFlowAliasOverrideHelp\",\"value\":\"Alias of authentication flow, which is triggered after first login with this identity provider. Term 'First Login' means that no Keycloak account is currently linked to the authenticated identity provider account.\"},{\"key\":\"importKeysSuccess\",\"value\":\"Keys successfully re-imported. Please save the provider to store the new certificates.\"},{\"key\":\"eventTypes.VERIFY_PROFILE_ERROR.description\",\"value\":\"Verify profile error\"},{\"key\":\"webOriginsHelp\",\"value\":\"Allowed CORS origins. To permit all origins of Valid Redirect URIs, add '+'. This does not include the '*' wildcard though. To permit all origins, explicitly add '*'.\"},{\"key\":\"